    Performance Improvements in .NET 5
    .NET 5中的性能改进

    Stephen Toub - MSFT

    July 13th, 202060 1
    2020年7月13日60 1

    In previous releases of .NET Core, I’ve blogged about the significant performance improvements that found their way into the release. For each post, from .NET Core 2.0 to .NET Core 2.1 to .NET Core 3.0, I found myself having more and more to talk about. Yet interestingly, after each I also found myself wondering whether there’d be enough meaningful improvements next time to warrant another post. Now that .NET 5 is shipping preview releases, I can definitively say the answer is, again, “yes”. .NET 5 has already seen a wealth of performance improvements, and even though it’s not scheduled for final release until later this year and there’s very likely to be a lot more improvements that find their way in by then, I wanted to highlight a bunch of the improvements that are already available now. In this post, I’ll highlight ~250 pull requests that have contributed to myriad of performance improvements across .NET 5.
    在以前的.NET Core发行版中，我在博客中介绍了该发行版中显著的性能改进。从.NET Core 2.0到.NET Core 2.1再到.NET Core 3.0的每一篇文章，我发现自己有越来越多的话题要谈。然而有趣的是，在每一次之后，我也发现自己想知道下一次是否有足够有意义的改进来保证另一个帖子。现在.NET 5发布了预览版，我可以肯定地说，再次，答案是“是的”。.NET 5已经看到了大量的性能改进，即使它直到今年晚些时候才计划最终发布，而且到那时很可能会有更多的改进，我想强调一下现在已经可用的一些改进。在这篇文章中，我将重点介绍250个拉取请求，这些请求对.NET 5中的无数性能改进做出了贡献。

    Setup 设置

    Benchmark.NET is now the canonical tool for measuring the performance of .NET code, making it simple to analyze the throughput and allocation of code snippets. As such, the majority of my examples in this post are measured using microbenchmarks written using that tool. To make it easy to follow-along at home (literally for many of us these days), I started by creating a directory and using the dotnet tool to scaffold it:
    Benchmark.NET现在是衡量.NET代码性能的标准工具，可以轻松分析代码段的吞吐量和分配。因此，我在这篇文章中的大多数示例都是使用使用该工具编写的微基准测试进行测量的。为了便于在家里使用（对我们许多人来说都是如此），我首先创建了一个目录，并使用 dotnet 工具来构建它：

    mkdir Benchmarks
cd Benchmarks
dotnet new console

    and I augmented the contents of the generated Benchmarks.csproj to look like the following:
    我将生成的Benchmarks.csproj的内容扩充为如下所示： 

    <Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
    <ServerGarbageCollection>true</ServerGarbageCollection>
    <TargetFrameworks>net5.0;netcoreapp3.1;net48</TargetFrameworks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="benchmarkdotnet" Version="0.12.1" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup Condition=" '$(TargetFramework)' == 'net48' ">
    <PackageReference Include="System.Memory" Version="4.5.4" />
    <PackageReference Include="System.Text.Json" Version="4.7.2" />
    <Reference Include="System.Net.Http" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>

    This lets me execute the benchmarks against .NET Framework 4.8, .NET Core 3.1, and .NET 5 (I currently have a nightly build installed for Preview 8). The .csproj also references the Benchmark.NET NuGet package (the latest release of which is version 12.1) in order to be able to use its features, and then references several other libraries and packages, specifically in support of being able to run tests on .NET Framework 4.8.
    这让我可以针对.NET Framework 4.8、.NET Core 3.1和.NET 5执行基准测试（我目前为Preview 8安装了一个夜间构建）。.csproj还引用了 Benchmark.NET NuGet包（其最新版本为12.1），以便能够使用其特性，然后引用了其他几个库和包，特别是为了支持能够在.NET Framework 4.8上运行测试。

    Then, I updated the generated Program.cs file in the same folder to look like this:
    然后，我更新了同一文件夹中生成的Program.cs文件，如下所示： 

    using BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes;

    // BENCHMARKS GO HERE
}

    and for each test, I copy/paste the benchmark code shown in each example to where it shows "// BENCHMARKS GO HERE".
    对于每个测试，我将每个示例中显示的基准代码复制/粘贴到显示 "// BENCHMARKS GO HERE" 的位置。

    To run the benchmarks, I then do:
    为了运行基准测试，我会这样做： 

    dotnet run -c Release -f net48 --runtimes net48 netcoreapp31 netcoreapp50 --filter ** --join

    This tells Benchmark.NET to:
    这告诉Benchmark.NET：

    • Build the benchmarks using the .NET Framework 4.8 surface area (which is the lowest-common denominator of all three targets and thus works for all of them).
      使用.NET Framework 4.8外围应用（这是所有三个目标的最小公分母，因此适用于所有目标）构建基准测试。
    • Run the benchmarks against each of .NET Framework 4.8, .NET Core 3.1, and .NET 5.
      针对.NET Framework 4.8、.NET Core 3.1和.NET 5运行基准。
    • Include all benchmarks in the assembly (don’t filter out any).
      在程序集中包含所有基准测试（不要过滤掉任何基准测试）。
    • Join the output together from all results from all benchmarks and display that at the end of the run (rather than interspersed throughout).
      将来自所有基准测试的所有结果的输出连接在一起，并在运行结束时显示出来（而不是散布在整个运行中）。

    In some cases where the API in question doesn’t exist for a particular target, I just leave off that part of the command-line.
    在某些情况下，如果某个特定的目标不存在所讨论的API，我只是忽略了命令行的这一部分。

    Finally, a few caveats:
    最后，有几点注意事项：

    • My last benchmarks post was about .NET Core 3.0. I didn’t write one about .NET Core 3.1 because, from a runtime and core libraries perspective, it saw relatively few improvements over its predecessor released just a few months prior. However, there were some improvements, on top of which in some cases we’ve already back-ported improvements made for .NET 5 back to .NET Core 3.1, where the changes were deemed impactful enough to warrant being added to the Long Term Support (LTS) release. As such, all of my comparisons here are against the latest .NET Core 3.1 servicing release (3.1.5) rather than against .NET Core 3.0.
      我的上一个基准测试帖子是关于.NET Core 3.0的。我没有写关于.NET Core 3.1的文章，因为从运行时和核心库的角度来看，它比几个月前发布的前一个版本有相对较少的改进。然而，也有一些改进，在某些情况下，我们已经将.NET 5的改进移植回.NET Core 3.1，这些更改被认为具有足够的影响力，足以保证被添加到长期支持（LTS）版本中。因此，我这里的所有比较都是针对最新的.NET Core 3.1服务版本（3.1.5），而不是针对.NET Core 3.0。
    • As the comparisons are about .NET 5 vs .NET Core 3.1, and as .NET Core 3.1 didn’t include the mono runtime, I’ve refrained from covering improvements made to mono, as well as to core library improvements specifically focused on “Blazor”. Thus when I refer to “the runtime”, I’m referring to coreclr, even though as of .NET 5 there are multiple runtimes under its umbrella, and all of them have been improved.
      由于比较是关于.NET 5与.NET Core 3.1的，并且由于.NET Core 3.1不包括mono运行时，因此我避免了对mono的改进，以及专门针对“Blazor”的核心库改进。因此，当我提到“运行时”时，我指的是coreclr，即使在.NET 5的保护伞下有多个运行时，并且所有这些都得到了改进。
    • Most of my examples were run on Windows, because I wanted to be able to compare against .NET Framework 4.8 as well. However, unless otherwise mentioned, all of the examples shown accrue equally to Windows, Linux, and macOS.
      我的大多数示例都是在Windows上运行的，因为我也希望能够与.NET Framework 4.8进行比较。然而，除非另有说明，所有显示的示例都同样适用于Windows，Linux和macOS。
    • The standard caveat: all measurements here are on my desktop machine, and your mileage may vary. Microbenchmarks can be very sensitive to any number of factors, including processor count, processor architecture, memory and cache speeds, and on and on. However, in general I’ve focused on performance improvements and included examples that should generally withstand any such differences.
      标准警告：这里所有的测量都是在我的台式机上进行的，你的里程可能会有所不同。微基准测试可能对许多因素非常敏感，包括处理器数量、处理器架构、内存和缓存速度等等。然而，总的来说，我关注的是性能改进，并包括一些通常能够承受任何此类差异的示例。

    Let’s get started… 我们开始吧。。

    GC

    For anyone interested in .NET and performance, garbage collection is frequently top of mind. Lots of effort goes into reducing allocation, not because the act of allocating is itself particularly expensive, but because of the follow-on costs in cleaning up after those allocations via the garbage collector (GC). No matter how much work goes into reducing allocations, however, the vast majority of workloads will incur them, and thus it’s important to continually push the boundaries of what the GC is able to accomplish, and how quickly.
    对于任何对.NET和性能感兴趣的人来说，垃圾收集通常是首要考虑的。在减少分配方面投入了大量精力，这并不是因为分配行为本身特别昂贵，而是因为在通过垃圾收集器（GC）进行这些分配之后进行清理的后续成本。然而，无论在减少分配方面投入多少工作，绝大多数工作负载都会产生这些工作负载，因此不断突破GC能够完成的任务以及速度的界限非常重要。

    This release has seen a lot of effort go into improving the GC. For example, dotnet/coreclr#25986 implements a form of work stealing for the “mark” phase of the GC. The .NET GC is a “tracing” collector, meaning that (at a very high level) when it runs it starts from a set of “roots” (known locations that are inherently reachable, such as a static field) and traverses from object to object, “marking” each as being reachable; after all such traversals, any objects not marked are unreachable and can be collected. This marking represents a significant portion of the time spent performing collections, and this PR improves marking performance by better balancing the work performed by each thread involved in the collection. When running with the “Server GC”, a thread per core is involved in collections, and as threads finish their allotted portions of the marking work, they’re now able to “steal” undone work from other threads in order to help the overall collection complete more quickly.
    在这个版本中，我们在改进GC方面做了很多努力。例如，dotnet/coreclr#25986为GC的“标记”阶段实现了一种形式的工作窃取。.NET GC是一个“跟踪”收集器，这意味着（在非常高的层次上）当它运行时，它从一组“根”（固有可到达的已知位置，例如静态字段）开始，并从对象到对象遍历，“标记”每个对象可到达;在所有这样的遍历之后，任何未标记的对象都是不可到达的，并且可以被收集。此标记代表了执行收集所花费的时间的很大一部分，并且此PR通过更好地平衡收集中涉及的每个线程所执行的工作来提高标记性能。当使用“服务器GC”运行时，每个核心的一个线程参与收集，并且当线程完成标记工作的分配部分时，它们现在能够从其他线程“窃取”未完成的工作，以帮助整体收集更快地完成。

    As another example, dotnet/runtime#35896 optimizes decommits on the “ephemeral” segment (gen0 and gen1 are referred to as “ephemeral” because they’re objects expected to last for only a short time). Decommitting is the act of giving pages of memory back to the operating system at the end of segments after the last live object on that segment. The question for the GC then becomes, when should such decommits happen, and how much should it decommit at any point in time, given that it may end up needing to allocate additional pages for additional allocations at some point in the near future.
    作为另一个例子，dotnet/runtime#35896优化了“短暂”段上的解压缩（gen 0和gen 1被称为“短暂”，因为它们是预期仅持续很短时间的对象）。解压缩是指在段的最后一个活动对象之后的段结束时将内存页返回给操作系统的行为。GC的问题就变成了，什么时候应该发生这样的解压缩，以及在任何时间点应该解压缩多少，因为在不久的将来，它可能最终需要为额外的分配分配额外的页面。

    Or take dotnet/runtime#32795, which improves the GC’s scalability on machines with higher core counts by reducing lock contention involved in the GC’s scanning of statics. Or dotnet/runtime#37894, which avoids costly memory resets (essentially telling the OS that the relevant memory is no longer interesting) unless the GC sees it’s in a low-memory situation. Or dotnet/runtime#37159, which (although not yet merged, is expected to be for .NET 5) builds on the work of @damageboy to vectorize sorting employed in the GC. Or dotnet/coreclr#27729, which reduces the time it takes for the GC to suspend threads, something that’s necessary in order for it to get a stable view so that it can accurately determine which are being used.
    或者以dotnet/runtime#32795为例，它通过减少GC静态数据扫描中涉及的锁争用，提高了GC在具有更高内核数的机器上的可伸缩性。或者dotnet/runtime#37894，它避免了昂贵的内存重置（本质上是告诉操作系统相关的内存不再感兴趣），除非GC发现它处于低内存的情况。或者dotnet/runtime#37159，它（虽然还没有合并，但预计将用于.NET 5）建立在@damageboy的工作基础上，以向量化GC中使用的排序。或者dotnet/coreclr#27729，它减少了GC挂起线程所需的时间，这对于它获得稳定的视图是必要的，这样它就可以准确地确定哪些线程正在使用。

    This is only a partial list of changes made to improve the GC itself, but that last bullet brings me to a topic of particular fascination for me, as it speaks to a lot of the work we’ve done in .NET in recent years. In this release, we’ve continued, and even accelerated, the process of porting native implementations in the coreclr runtime from C/C++ to instead be normal C# managed code in System.Private.Corelib. Such a move has a plethora of benefits, including making it much easier for us to share a single implementation across multiple runtimes (like coreclr and mono), and even making it easier for us to evolve API surface area, such as by reusing the same logic to handle both arrays and spans. But one thing that takes some folks by surprise is that such benefits also include performance, in multiple ways. One such way harkens back to one of the original motivations for using a managed runtime: safety. By default, code written in C# is “safe”, in that the runtime ensures all memory accesses are bounds checked, and only by explicit action visible in the code (e.g. using the unsafe keyword, the Marshal class, the Unsafe class, etc.) is a developer able to remove such validation. As a result, as maintainers of an open source project, our job of shipping a secure system is made significantly easier when contributions come in the form of managed code: while such code can of course contain bugs that might slip through code reviews and automated testing, we can sleep better at night knowing that the chances for such bugs to introduce security problems are drastically reduced. That in turn means we’re more likely to accept improvements to managed code and at a higher velocity, with it being faster for a contributor to provide and faster for us to help validate. We’ve also found a larger number of contributors interested in exploring performance improvements when it comes in the form of C# rather than C. And more experimentation from more people progressing at a faster rate yields better performance.
    这只是改进GC本身的部分更改列表，但最后一个项目带我到了一个对我特别感兴趣的话题，因为它涉及到了我们近年来在.NET中所做的很多工作。在这个版本中，我们继续甚至加速了将coreclr运行时中的本机实现从C/C++移植到System. Private. Corlib中的普通C#托管代码的过程。这样的举动有很多好处，包括让我们更容易在多个运行时（如coreclr和mono）中共享单个实现，甚至让我们更容易发展API表面区域，例如通过重用相同的逻辑来处理数组和跨度。但有一件事让一些人感到惊讶，那就是这样的好处还包括性能，在多种方面。其中一种方法可以追溯到使用托管运行时的最初动机之一：安全为代价的 默认情况下，用C#编写的代码是“安全的”，因为运行时确保所有内存访问都是边界检查的，并且只有通过代码中可见的显式操作（例如使用 unsafe 关键字、 Marshal 类、 Unsafe 类等）开发人员是否能够移除这种验证。因此，作为一个开源项目的维护者，当我们以托管代码的形式提供贡献时，我们发布安全系统的工作会变得非常容易：虽然这样的代码当然可以包含可能通过代码审查和自动测试的bug，但是我们可以在晚上睡得更好，因为知道这样的bug引入安全问题的机会大大减少了。这反过来意味着我们更有可能接受对托管代码的改进，并且速度更快，贡献者提供的速度更快，我们帮助验证的速度也更快。 我们还发现有更多的贡献者有兴趣探索C#而不是C的性能改进。更多的人以更快的速度进行更多的实验，会产生更好的性能。

    There are, however, more direct forms of performance improvements we’ve seen from such porting. There is a relatively small amount of overhead required for managed code to call into the runtime, but when such calls are made at high frequency, such overhead adds up. Consider dotnet/coreclr#27700, which moved the implementation of the sorting of arrays of primitive types out of native code in coreclr and up into C# in Corelib. In addition to that code then powering new public APIs for sorting spans, it also made it cheaper to sort smaller arrays where the cost of doing so is dominated by the transition from managed code. We can see this with a small benchmark, which is just using Array.Sort to sort int[], double[], and string[] arrays of 10 items:
    然而，我们已经从这种移植中看到了更直接的性能改进形式。托管代码调用运行库所需的开销相对较小，但当此类调用以高频率进行时，此类开销就会增加。考虑一下dotnet/coreclr#27700，它将原始类型数组排序的实现从coreclr的本地代码中移到了Corelib的C#中。除了这些代码为排序跨度的新公共API提供动力之外，它还使得排序较小的数组变得更便宜，而这样做的成本主要是从托管代码过渡。我们可以通过一个小的基准测试来看到这一点，它只是使用 Array.Sort 对10个元素的 int[] 、 double[] 和 string[] 数组进行排序：

    public class DoubleSorting : Sorting<double> { protected override double GetNext() => _random.Next(); }
public class Int32Sorting : Sorting<int> { protected override int GetNext() => _random.Next(); }
public class StringSorting : Sorting<string>
{
    protected override string GetNext()
    {
        var dest = new char[_random.Next(1, 5)];
        for (int i = 0; i < dest.Length; i++) dest[i] = (char)('a' + _random.Next(26));
        return new string(dest);
    }
}

public abstract class Sorting<T>
{
    protected Random _random;
    private T[] _orig, _array;

    [Params(10)]
    public int Size { get; set; }

    protected abstract T GetNext();

    [GlobalSetup]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _random = new Random(42);
        _orig = Enumerable.Range(0, Size).Select(_ => GetNext()).ToArray();
        _array = (T[])_orig.Clone();
        Array.Sort(_array);
    }

    [Benchmark]
    public void Random()
    {
        _orig.AsSpan().CopyTo(_array);
        Array.Sort(_array);
    }
}

    This in and of itself is a nice benefit of the move, as is the fact that in .NET 5 via dotnet/runtime#37630 we also added System.Half, a new 16-bit floating-point primitive, and being in managed code, this sorting implementation’s optimizations almost immediately applied to it, whereas the previous native implementation would have required significant additional work, with no C++ standard type for half. But, there’s an arguably even more impactful performance benefit here, and it brings us back to where I started this discussion: GC.
    这本身就是迁移的一个很好的好处，事实上，在.NET 5中，通过dotnet/runtime#37630，我们还添加了 System.Half ，一个新的16位浮点原语，并且在托管代码中，排序实现的优化几乎立即应用于它，而之前的原生实现将需要大量额外的工作，没有C++标准类型的 half 。但是，这里有一个可以说是更有影响力的性能优势，它把我们带回到我开始讨论的地方：GC.

    One of the interesting metrics for the GC is “pause time”, which effectively means how long the GC must pause the runtime in order to perform its work. Longer pause times have a direct impact on latency, which can be a crucial metric for all manner of workloads. As alluded to earlier, the GC may need to suspend threads in order to get a consistent view of the world and to ensure that it can move objects around safely, but if a thread is currently executing C/C++ code in the runtime, the GC may need to wait until that call completes before it’s able to suspend the thread. Thus, the more work we can do in managed code instead of native code, the better off we are for GC pause times. We can use the same Array.Sort example to see this. Consider this program:
    GC的一个有趣的度量标准是“暂停时间”，它实际上意味着GC为了执行其工作必须暂停运行时多长时间。更长的暂停时间对延迟有直接影响，延迟对于各种工作负载来说都是一个关键的指标。正如前面提到的，GC可能需要挂起线程，以便获得一致的世界视图，并确保它可以安全地移动对象，但是如果线程当前正在运行时执行C/C++代码，GC可能需要等到调用完成后才能够挂起线程。因此，我们可以在托管代码而不是本机代码中做的工作越多，GC暂停时间就越好。我们可以使用相同的 Array.Sort 示例来查看这一点。考虑这个程序：

    using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using System.Threading;

class Program
{
    public static void Main()
    {
        new Thread(() =>
        {
            var a = new int[20];
            while (true) Array.Sort(a);
        }) { IsBackground = true }.Start();

        var sw = new Stopwatch();
        while (true)
        {
            sw.Restart();
            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)
            {
                GC.Collect();
                Thread.Sleep(15);
            }
            Console.WriteLine(sw.Elapsed.TotalSeconds);
        }
    }
}

    This is spinning up a thread that just sits in a tight loop sorting a small array over and over, while on the main thread it performs 10 GCs, each with approximately 15 milliseconds between them. So, we’d expect that loop to take a little more than 150 milliseconds. But when I run this on .NET Core 3.1, I get numbers of seconds like this:
    这是一个线程，它只是坐在一个紧密的循环中，一遍又一遍地排序一个小数组，而在主线程上，它执行10个GC，每个GC之间大约有15毫秒。所以，我们预计这个循环需要150毫秒多一点。但是当我在.NET Core 3.1上运行时，我得到的秒数是这样的： 

    6.6419048
5.5663149
5.7430339
6.032052
7.8892468

    The GC has difficulty here interrupting the thread performing the sorts, causing the GC pause times to be way higher than desirable. Thankfully, when I instead run this on .NET 5, I get numbers like this:
    GC在这里很难中断执行排序的线程，导致GC暂停时间远远超过预期。值得庆幸的是，当我在.NET 5上运行它时，我得到了这样的数字： 

    0.159311
0.159453
0.1594669
0.1593328
0.1586566

    which is exactly what we predicted we should get. By moving the Array.Sort implementation into managed code, where the runtime can more easily suspend the implementation when it wants to, we’ve made it possible for the GC to be much better at its job.
    这正是我们预测的结果。通过将Array.sort实现移到托管代码中，运行时可以在需要时更容易地挂起实现，我们已经使GC能够更好地完成其工作。

    This isn’t limited to just Array.Sort, of course. A bunch of PRs performed such porting, for example dotnet/runtime#32722 moving the stdelemref and ldelemaref JIT helpers to C#, dotnet/runtime#32353 moving portions of the unbox helper to C# (and instrumenting the rest with appropriate GC polling locations that let the GC suspend appropriately in the rest), dotnet/coreclr#27603 / dotnet/coreclr#27634 / dotnet/coreclr#27123 / dotnet/coreclr#27776 moving more array implementations like Array.Clear and Array.Copy to C#, dotnet/coreclr#27216 moving more of Buffer to C#, and dotnet/coreclr#27792 moving Enum.CompareTo to C#. Some of these changes then enabled subsequent gains, such as with dotnet/runtime#32342 and dotnet/runtime#35733, which employed the improvements in Buffer.Memmove to achieve additional gains in various string and Array methods.
    当然，这并不局限于 Array.Sort 。一堆PR执行了这样的移植，例如dotnet/runtime#32722将 stdelemref 和 ldelemaref JIT助手移动到C#，dotnet/runtime#32353将 unbox 助手的一部分移动到C#（并且用适当的GC轮询位置对其余部分进行仪表化，该位置允许GC在其余部分中适当地挂起），dotnet/coreclr#27603 / dotnet/coreclr#27634 / dotnet/coreclr#27123 / dotnet/coreclr#27776将更多的数组实现（如 Array.Clear 和 Array.Copy ）迁移到C#，dotnet/coreclr#27216将更多的 Buffer 迁移到C#，dotnet/coreclr#27792将 Enum.CompareTo 迁移到C#。这些变化中的一些随后实现了后续的增益，例如dotnet/runtime#32342和dotnet/runtime#35733，它们采用了 Buffer.Memmove 中的改进，以在各种 string 和 Array 方法中实现额外的增益。

    As one final thought on this set of changes, another interesting thing to note is how micro-optimizations made in one release may be based on assumptions that are later invalidated, and when employing such micro-optimizations, one needs to be ready and willing to adapt. In my .NET Core 3.0 blog post, I called out “peanut butter” changes like dotnet/coreclr#21756, which switched lots of call sites from using Array.Copy(source, destination, length) to instead use Array.Copy(source, sourceOffset, destination, destinationOffset, length), because the overhead involved in the former getting the lower bounds of the source and destination arrays was measurable. But with the aforementioned set of changes that moved array-processing code to C#, the simpler overload’s overheads disappeared, making it both the simpler and faster choice for these operations. And such, for .NET 5 PRs dotnet/coreclr#27641 and dotnet/corefx#42343 switched all of these call sites and more back to using the simpler overload. dotnet/runtime#36304 is another example of undoing previous optimizations due to changes that made them obsolete or actually harmful. You’ve always been able to pass a single character to String.Split, e.g. version.Split('.'). The problem, however, was the only overload of Split that this could bind to was Split(params char[] separator), which means that every such call resulted in the C# compiler generating a char[] allocation. To work around that, previous releases saw caches added, allocating arrays ahead of time and storing them into statics that could then be used by Split calls to avoid the per-call char[]. Now that there’s a Split(char separator, StringSplitOptions options = StringSplitOptions.None) overload in .NET, we no longer need the array at all.
    作为对这组变化的最后一个想法，另一个值得注意的有趣的事情是，在一个版本中进行的微优化可能是基于后来被无效的假设，并且当使用这样的微优化时，需要准备好并愿意适应。在我的.NET Core 3.0博客文章中，我提出了“花生酱”的变化，如dotnet/coreclr#21756，它将许多调用站点从使用 Array.Copy(source, destination, length) 改为使用 Array.Copy(source, sourceOffset, destination, destinationOffset, length) ，因为前者获取源和目标数组的下限所涉及的开销是可测量的。但是，通过前面提到的将数组处理代码转移到C#的一系列更改，更简单的重载的开销消失了，使其成为这些操作的更简单和更快的选择。因此，对于.NET 5 PR，dotnet/coreclr#27641和dotnet/corefx#42343将所有这些调用站点切换到使用更简单的重载。 dotnet/runtime#36304是另一个撤消以前优化的例子，因为更改使它们过时或实际上有害。您总是可以向 String.Split 传递单个字符，例如：三号。然而，问题是，它可以绑定的 Split 的唯一重载是 Split(params char[] separator) ，这意味着每次这样的调用都会导致C#编译器生成 char[] 分配。为了解决这个问题，以前的版本增加了缓存，提前分配数组并将它们存储到静态中，然后可以由 Split 调用使用，以避免每次调用 char[] 。既然.NET中有一个 Split(char separator, StringSplitOptions options = StringSplitOptions.None) 重载，我们就不再需要数组了。

    As one last example, I showed how moving code out of the runtime and into managed code can help with GC pauses, but there are of course other ways code remaining in the runtime can help with that. dotnet/runtime#36179 reduced GC pauses due to exception handling by ensuring the runtime was in preemptive mode around code such as getting “Watson” bucket parameters (basically, a set of data that uniquely identifies this particular exception and call stack for reporting purposes).
    作为最后一个例子，我展示了如何将代码移出运行库并移入托管代码可以帮助处理GC暂停，当然还有其他方法将代码保留在运行库中也可以帮助处理。dotnet/runtime#36179通过确保运行时在代码周围处于抢占模式，例如获取“沃森”桶参数（基本上，一组唯一标识此特定异常的数据和用于报告目的的调用堆栈），减少了由于异常处理而导致的GC暂停。

    JIT

    .NET 5 is an exciting version for the Just-In-Time (JIT) compiler, too, with many improvements of all manner finding their way into the release. As with any compiler, improvements made to the JIT can have wide-reaching effects. Often individual changes have a small impact on an individual piece of code, but such changes are then magnified by the sheer number of places they apply.
    .NET 5也是一个令人兴奋的即时（JIT）编译器版本，在发布中有许多各种改进。与任何编译器一样，对JIT的改进可以产生广泛的影响。通常，单个更改对单个代码片段的影响很小，但是这样的更改会被它们应用的地方数量放大。

    There is an almost unbounded number of optimizations that can be added to the JIT, and given an unlimited amount of time to run such optimizations, the JIT could create the most optimal code for any given scenario. But the JIT doesn’t have an unbounded amount of time. The “just-in-time” nature of the JIT means it’s performing the compilation as the app runs: when a method that hasn’t yet been compiled is invoked, the JIT needs to provide the assembly code for it on-demand. That means the thread can’t make forward progress until the compilation has completed, which in turn means the JIT needs to be strategic in what optimizations it applies and how it chooses to use its limited time budget. Various techniques are used to give the JIT more time, such as using “ahead of time” compilation (AOT) on some portions of the app to do as much of the compilation work as is possible before the app is executed (for example, the core libraries are all AOT compiled using a technology named “ReadyToRun”, which you may hear referred to as “R2R” or even “crossgen”, which is the tool that produces these images), or by using “tiered compilation”, which allows the JIT to initially compile a method with few-to-no optimizations applied and thus be very fast in doing so, and only spend more time recompiling it with many more optimizations when it’s deemed valuable, namely when the method is shown to be used repeatedly. However, more generally the developers contributing to the JIT simply choose to use the allotted time budget for optimizations that prove to be valuable given the code developers are writing and the code patterns they’re employing. That means that as .NET evolves and gains new capabilities, new language features, and new library features, the JIT also evolves with optimizations suited to the newer style of code being written.
    可以添加到JIT中的优化数量几乎是无限的，并且给定无限量的时间来运行这样的优化，JIT可以为任何给定的场景创建最优化的代码。但是JIT没有无限的时间。JIT的“即时”特性意味着它在应用运行时执行编译：当一个尚未编译的方法被调用时，JIT需要按需为其提供汇编代码。这意味着线程在编译完成之前不能向前推进，这反过来又意味着JIT需要在应用什么优化以及如何选择使用其有限的时间预算方面具有战略性。 使用了各种技术来给予JIT更多的时间，例如使用“提前”编译（AOT）在应用程序的某些部分上完成尽可能多的编译工作（例如，核心库都是使用名为“ReadyToRun”的技术进行AOT编译的，您可能会听到将其称为“R2R”甚至“crossgen”，它是产生这些图像的工具），或者通过使用“分层编译”，这允许JIT最初编译一个应用很少到没有应用优化的方法，因此在这样做时非常快，并且仅在认为有价值时花费更多的时间用更多的优化来重新编译它，即当该方法被显示为重复使用时。然而，更一般地，为JIT做出贡献的开发人员只是选择使用分配的时间预算来进行优化，考虑到开发人员正在编写的代码和他们正在使用的代码模式，这些优化被证明是有价值的。这意味着作为。NET发展并获得了新的功能、新的语言特性和新的库特性，JIT也发展了适合于编写的新代码风格的优化。

    A great example of that is with dotnet/runtime#32538 from @benaadams. Span<T> has been permeating all layers of the .NET stack, as developers working on the runtime, core libraries, ASP.NET Core, and beyond recognize its power when it comes to writing safe and efficient code that also unifies handling for strings, managed arrays, natively-allocated memory, and other forms of data. Similarly, value types (structs) are being used much more pervasively as a way to avoid object allocation overheads via stack allocation. But this heavy reliance on such types also introduces additional headaches for the runtime. The coreclr runtime uses a “precise” garbage collector, which means the GC is able to track with 100% accuracy what values refer to managed objects and what values don’t; that has benefits, but it also has cost (in contrast, the mono runtime uses a “conservative” garbage collector, which has some performance benefits, but also means it may interpret an arbitrary value on the stack that happens to be the same as a managed object’s address as being a live reference to that object). One such cost is that the JIT needs to help the GC by guaranteeing that any local that could be interpreted as an object reference is zero’d out prior to the GC paying attention to it; otherwise, the GC could end up seeing a garbage value in a local that hadn’t been set yet, and assume it referred to a valid object, at which point “bad things” can happen. The more reference locals there are, the more clearing needs to be done. If you’re just clearing a few locals, it’s probably not noticeable. But as the number increases, the amount of time spent clearing those locals can add up, especially in a small method used in a very hot code path. This situation has become much more common with spans and structs, where coding patterns often result in many more references (a Span<T> contains a reference) that need to be zero’d. The aforementioned PR addressed this by updating the JIT’s generated code for the prolog blocks that perform this zero’ing to use xmm registers rather than using the rep stosd instruction. Effectively, it vectorized the zeroing. You can see the impact of this with the following benchmark:
    一个很好的例子是来自@benaadams的dotnet/runtime#32538。 Span<T> 已经渗透到.NET堆栈的所有层，因为在运行时、核心库、ASP.NET Core等领域工作的开发人员认识到它在编写安全高效的代码时的强大力量，这些代码还统一了字符串、托管数组、本地分配内存和其他形式的数据处理。类似地，值类型（结构体）正被更广泛地用作通过堆栈分配来避免对象分配开销的一种方式。但是这种对此类类型的严重依赖也给运行时带来了额外的麻烦。 coreclr运行时使用一个“精确”的垃圾收集器，这意味着GC能够100%准确地跟踪哪些值引用托管对象，哪些值不引用托管对象;这有好处，但也有代价（相比之下，mono运行时使用“保守”垃圾收集器，这有一些性能好处，但也意味着它可以将堆栈上碰巧与托管对象地址相同的任意值解释为对该对象的实时引用）。一个这样的代价是JIT需要帮助GC，确保任何可以被解释为对象引用的局部在GC注意它之前被清零;否则，GC可能最终会在一个尚未设置的本地文件中看到一个垃圾值，并假设它引用了一个有效的对象，这时可能会发生“坏事情”。引用局部变量越多，需要进行的清除就越多。如果你只是清除一些当地人，可能不会引起注意。 但是随着数量的增加，清除这些局部变量所花费的时间会增加，特别是在非常热的代码路径中使用的小方法中。这种情况在span和struct中变得更加常见，编码模式通常会导致更多的引用（一个 Span<T> 包含一个引用），这些引用需要为零。上述PR通过更新JIT生成的用于执行该归零的序言块的代码以使用 xmm 寄存器而不是使用 rep stosd 指令来解决这个问题。实际上，它将归零矢量化。 您可以通过以下基准来看到这一点的影响：

    [Benchmark]
public int Zeroing()
{
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s1 = "hello world";
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s2 = Nop(s1);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s3 = Nop(s2);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s4 = Nop(s3);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s5 = Nop(s4);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s6 = Nop(s5);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s7 = Nop(s6);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s8 = Nop(s7);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s9 = Nop(s8);
    ReadOnlySpan<char> s10 = Nop(s9);
    return s1.Length + s2.Length + s3.Length + s4.Length + s5.Length + s6.Length + s7.Length + s8.Length + s9.Length + s10.Length;
}

[MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.NoInlining)]
private static ReadOnlySpan<char> Nop(ReadOnlySpan<char> span) => default;

    On my machine, I get results like the following:
    在我的机器上，我得到如下结果：

    Method 方法 Runtime 运行时 Mean 意味 Ratio 比
    Zeroing 归零 .NET FW 4.8 22.85 ns 22.85纳秒 1.00
    Zeroing 归零 .NET Core 3.1 18.60 ns 0.81
    Zeroing 归零 .NET 5.0 15.07 ns 15.07纳秒 0.66

    Note that such zero’ing is actually needed in more situations than I mentioned. In particular, by default the C# specification requires that all locals be initialized to their default values before the developer’s code is executed. You can see this with an example like this:
    请注意，实际上在比我提到的更多的情况下需要这样的归零。特别是，默认情况下，C#规范要求在执行开发人员代码之前将所有局部变量初始化为它们的默认值。你可以通过这样的例子看到这一点： 

    using System;
using System.Runtime.CompilerServices;
using System.Threading;

unsafe class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        while (true)
        {
            Example();
            Thread.Sleep(1);
        }
    }

    [MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.NoInlining)]
    static void Example()
    {
        Guid g;
        Console.WriteLine(*&g);
    }
}

    Run that, and you should see only Guids of all 0s output. That’s because the C# compiler is emitting a .locals init flag into the IL for the compiled Example method, and that .locals init tells the JIT it needs to zero out all locals, not just those that contain references. However, in .NET 5, there’s a new attribute in the runtime (dotnet/runtime#454):
    运行它，您应该只看到所有#1输出中的#0。这是因为C#编译器为编译后的 Example 方法向IL发送一个 .locals init 标志，而 .locals init 告诉JIT它需要将所有局部变量归零，而不仅仅是那些包含引用的局部变量。然而，在.NET 5中，运行时中有一个新属性（dotnet/runtime#454）：

    namespace System.Runtime.CompilerServices
{
    [AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Module | AttributeTargets.Class | AttributeTargets.Struct | AttributeTargets.Constructor | AttributeTargets.Method | AttributeTargets.Property | AttributeTargets.Event | AttributeTargets.Interface, Inherited = false)]
    public sealed class SkipLocalsInitAttribute : Attribute { }
}

    This attribute is recognized by the C# compiler and is used to tell the compiler to not emit the .locals init when it otherwise would have. If we make a small tweak to the previous example, adding the attribute to the whole module:
    这个属性被C#编译器识别，并用于告诉编译器不要在其他情况下发出 .locals init 。如果我们对前面的示例做一个小的调整，将属性添加到整个模块中：

    using System;
using System.Runtime.CompilerServices;
using System.Threading;

[module: SkipLocalsInit]

unsafe class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        while (true)
        {
            Example();
            Thread.Sleep(1);
        }
    }

    [MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.NoInlining)]
    static void Example()
    {
        Guid g;
        Console.WriteLine(*&g);
    }
}

    you should now see different results, in particular you should very likely see non-zero Guids. As of dotnet/runtime#37541, the core libraries in .NET 5 all use this attribute now to disable .locals init (in previous releases, .locals init was stripped out by a post-compilation step employed when building the core libraries). Note that the C# compiler only allows SkipLocalsInit to be used in unsafe contexts, because it can easily result in corruption in code that hasn’t been appropriately validated for its use (so be thoughtful if / when you apply it).
    您现在应该看到不同的结果，特别是您应该很可能看到非零的 Guid 。从dotnet/runtime#37541开始，.NET 5中的核心库现在都使用这个属性来禁用 .locals init （在以前的版本中， .locals init 被构建核心库时使用的后期编译步骤剥离）。请注意，C#编译器只允许在 unsafe 上下文中使用 SkipLocalsInit ，因为它很容易导致代码的损坏，而代码没有经过适当的验证（所以如果/当你应用它时，请仔细考虑）。

    In addition to making zero’ing faster, there also have been changes to remove the zero’ing entirely. For example, dotnet/runtime#31960, dotnet/runtime#36918, dotnet/runtime#37786, and dotnet/runtime#38314 all contributed to removing zero’ing when the JIT could prove it to be duplicative.
    除了使归零更快之外，还存在完全去除归零的改变。例如，dotnet/runtime#31960、dotnet/runtime#36918、dotnet/runtime#37786和dotnet/runtime#38314都有助于在JIT可以证明它是重复的时候删除置零。

    Such zero’ing is an example of a tax incurred for managed code, with the runtime needing it in order to provide guarantees of its model and of the requirements of the languages above it. Another such tax is bounds checking. One of the great advantages of using managed code is that a whole class of potential security vulnerabilities are made irrelevant by default. The runtime ensures that indexing into arrays, strings, and spans is bounds-checked, meaning the runtime injects checks to ensure that the index being requested is within the bounds of the data being indexed (i.e. greater than or equal to zero and less then the length of the data). Here’s a simple example:
    这种归零是托管代码产生的税的一个示例，运行时需要它，以便提供对其模型和其上的语言的要求的保证。另一种税收是边界检查。使用托管代码的一大优势是，默认情况下，一整类潜在安全漏洞都不相关。运行时确保对数组、字符串和span的索引是边界检查的，这意味着运行时注入检查以确保所请求的索引在所索引的数据的边界内（即，大于或等于零且小于数据的长度）。下面是一个简单的例子： 

    public static char Get(string s, int i) => s[i];

    For this code to be safe, the runtime needs to generate a check that i falls within the bounds of string s, which the JIT does by using assembly like the following:
    为了使代码安全，运行时需要生成一个检查 i 福尔斯字符串 s 的范围内，JIT通过使用汇编来完成这一检查，如下所示：

    ; Program.Get(System.String, Int32)
       sub       rsp,28
       cmp       edx,[rcx+8]
       jae       short M01_L00
       movsxd    rax,edx
       movzx     eax,word ptr [rcx+rax*2+0C]
       add       rsp,28
       ret
M01_L00:
       call      CORINFO_HELP_RNGCHKFAIL
       int       3
; Total bytes of code 28

    This assembly was generated via a handy feature of Benchmark.NET: add [DisassemblyDiagnoser] to the class containing the benchmarks, and it spits out the disassembled assembly code. We can see that the assembly takes the string (passed via the rcx register) and loads the string’s length (which is stored 8 bytes into the object, hence the [rcx+8]), comparing that with i passed in the edx register, and if with an unsigned comparison (unsigned so that any negative values wrap around to be larger than the length) i is greater than or equal to the length, jumping to a helper COREINFO_HELP_RNGCHKFAIL that throws an exception. Just a few instructions, but certain kinds of code can spend a lot of cycles indexing, and thus it’s helpful when the JIT can eliminate as many of the bounds checks as it can prove to be unnecessary.
    这个程序集是通过Benchmark.NET的一个方便功能生成的：将 [DisassemblyDiagnoser] 添加到包含基准测试的类中，它会吐出反汇编的汇编代码。我们可以看到，程序集取字符串（通过 rcx 寄存器传递）并加载字符串的长度（它存储了8个字节到对象中，因此是 [rcx+8] ），将其与在 edx 寄存器中传递的 i 进行比较，如果与无符号比较（无符号，以便任何负值绕到大于长度） i 大于或等于长度，跳转到抛出异常的帮助器 COREINFO_HELP_RNGCHKFAIL 。只有一些指令，但某些类型的代码可能会花费大量的周期来索引，因此JIT可以消除尽可能多的边界检查，因为它可以证明是不必要的。

    The JIT has already been capable of removing bounds checks in a variety of situations. For example, when you write the loop:
    JIT已经能够消除各种情况下的边界检查。例如，当你编写循环时： 

    int[] arr = ...;
for (int i = 0; i < arr.Length; i++)
    Use(arr[i]);

    the JIT can prove that i will never be outside the bounds of the array, and so it can elide the bounds checks it would otherwise generate. In .NET 5, it can remove bounds checking in more places. For example, consider this function that writes the bytes of an integer as characters to a span:
    JIT可以证明 i 永远不会在数组的边界之外，因此它可以省略否则将生成的边界检查。在.NET 5中，它可以在更多地方删除边界检查。例如，考虑这个函数，它将整数的字节作为字符写入span：

    private static bool TryToHex(int value, Span<char> span)
{
    if ((uint)span.Length <= 7)
        return false;

    ReadOnlySpan<byte> map = new byte[] { (byte)'0', (byte)'1', (byte)'2', (byte)'3', (byte)'4', (byte)'5', (byte)'6', (byte)'7', (byte)'8', (byte)'9', (byte)'A', (byte)'B', (byte)'C', (byte)'D', (byte)'E', (byte)'F' }; ;
    span[0] = (char)map[(value >> 28) & 0xF];
    span[1] = (char)map[(value >> 24) & 0xF];
    span[2] = (char)map[(value >> 20) & 0xF];
    span[3] = (char)map[(value >> 16) & 0xF];
    span[4] = (char)map[(value >> 12) & 0xF];
    span[5] = (char)map[(value >> 8) & 0xF];
    span[6] = (char)map[(value >> 4) & 0xF];
    span[7] = (char)map[value & 0xF];
    return true;
}

private char[] _buffer = new char[100];

[Benchmark]
public bool BoundsChecking() => TryToHex(int.MaxValue, _buffer);

    First, in this example it’s worth noting we’re relying on a C# compiler optimization. Note the:
    首先，在这个例子中值得注意的是，我们依赖于C#编译器优化。注意： 

    ReadOnlySpan<byte> map = new byte[] { (byte)'0', (byte)'1', (byte)'2', (byte)'3', (byte)'4', (byte)'5', (byte)'6', (byte)'7', (byte)'8', (byte)'9', (byte)'A', (byte)'B', (byte)'C', (byte)'D', (byte)'E', (byte)'F' };

    That looks terribly expensive, like we’re allocating a byte array on each call to TryToHex. In fact, it’s not, and it’s actually better than if we had done:
    这看起来非常昂贵，就像我们在每次调用 TryToHex 时分配一个字节数组一样。事实上，它不是，它实际上比我们做的更好：

    private static readonly byte[] s_map = new byte[] { (byte)'0', (byte)'1', (byte)'2', (byte)'3', (byte)'4', (byte)'5', (byte)'6', (byte)'7', (byte)'8', (byte)'9', (byte)'A', (byte)'B', (byte)'C', (byte)'D', (byte)'E', (byte)'F' };
...
ReadOnlySpan<byte> map = s_map;

    The C# compiler recognizes the pattern of a new byte array being assigned directly to a ReadOnlySpan<byte> (it also recognizes sbyte and bool, but nothing larger than a byte because of endianness concerns). Because the array nature is then completely hidden by the span, the C# compiler emits that by actually storing the bytes into the assembly’s data section, and the span is just created by wrapping it around a pointer to the static data and the length:
    C#编译器识别一个新的字节数组被直接分配给 ReadOnlySpan<byte> 的模式（它也识别 sbyte 和 bool ，但由于字节顺序的问题，没有比字节大的）。因为数组的性质随后被span完全隐藏，C#编译器通过将字节实际存储到程序集的数据部分来发出，而span只是通过将其包装在指向静态数据和长度的指针周围来创建：

    IL_000c: ldsflda valuetype '<PrivateImplementationDetails>'/'__StaticArrayInitTypeSize=16' '<PrivateImplementationDetails>'::'2125B2C332B1113AAE9BFC5E9F7E3B4C91D828CB942C2DF1EEB02502ECCAE9E9'
IL_0011: ldc.i4.s 16
IL_0013: newobj instance void valuetype [System.Runtime]System.ReadOnlySpan'1<uint8>::.ctor(void*, int32)

    This is important for this JIT discussion, because of that ldc.i4.s 16 in the above. That’s the IL loading the length of 16 to use to create the span, and the JIT can see that. It knows then that the span has a length of 16, which means if it can prove that an access is always to a value greater than or equal to 0 and less than 16, it needn’t bounds check that access. dotnet/runtime#1644 did exactly that, recognizing patterns like array[index % const], and eliding the bounds check when the const was less than or equal to the length. In the previous TryToHex example, the JIT can see that the map span has a length of 16, and it can see that all of the indexing into it is done with & 0xF, meaning all values will end up being in range, and thus it can eliminate all of the bounds checks on map. Combine that with the fact that it could already see that no bounds checking is needed on the writes into the span (because it could see the length check earlier in the method guarded all of the indexing into span), and this whole method is bounds-check-free in .NET 5. On my machine, this benchmark yields results like the following:
    这对于这个JIT讨论很重要，因为上面的 ldc.i4.s 16 。这是IL加载长度为16的代码，用于创建跨度，JIT可以看到这一点。然后它知道跨度的长度为16，这意味着如果它可以证明访问总是大于或等于0且小于16的值，它就不需要对访问进行边界检查。dotnet/runtime#1644正是这样做的，识别像 array[index % const] 这样的模式，并在 const 小于或等于长度时省略边界检查。在前面的 TryToHex 示例中，JIT可以看到 map 跨度的长度为16，并且它可以看到对它的所有索引都是用 & 0xF 完成的，这意味着所有值最终都将在范围内，因此它可以消除对 map 的所有边界检查。 联合收割机这一点，它已经可以看到对 span 的写入不需要进行边界检查（因为它可以在保护到 span 的所有索引的方法中看到更早的长度检查），整个方法在.NET 5中是无边界检查的。 在我的机器上，这个基准测试产生如下结果：

    Another nice bounds checking removal comes from @nathan-moore in dotnet/runtime#36263. I mentioned that the JIT is already able to remove bounds checking for the very common pattern of iterating from 0 to the array, string, or span’s length, but there are variations on this that are also relatively common but that weren’t previously recognized. For example, consider this microbenchmark which calls a method that detects whether a span of integers is sorted:
    另一个不错的边界检查删除来自dotnet/runtime#36263中的@nathan-moore。我提到JIT已经能够消除从0迭代到数组、字符串或span长度的非常常见的模式的边界检查，但也有一些变体，这些变体也是相对常见的，但以前没有被认识到。例如，考虑一下这个微基准测试，它调用一个方法来检测整数范围是否被排序：

    private int[] _array = Enumerable.Range(0, 1000).ToArray();

[Benchmark]
public bool IsSorted() => IsSorted(_array);

private static bool IsSorted(ReadOnlySpan<int> span)
{
    for (int i = 0; i < span.Length - 1; i++)
        if (span[i] > span[i + 1])
            return false;

    return true;
}

    This slight variation from the recognized pattern was enough previously to prevent the JIT from eliding the bounds checks. Not anymore. .NET 5 on my machine is able to execute this 20% faster:
    这种与识别模式的微小变化在以前就足以阻止JIT省略边界检查。不再是了.NET 5在我的机器上执行此操作的速度提高了20%：

    Another case where the JIT ensures checks are in place for a category of error are null checks. The JIT does this in coordination with the runtime, with the JIT ensuring appropriate instructions are in place to incur hardware exceptions and with the runtime then translating such faults into .NET exceptions (e.g. here). But sometimes instructions are necessary only for null checks rather than also accomplishing other necessary functionality, and as long as the required null check happens due to some instruction, the unnecessary duplicative ones can be removed. Consider this code:
    JIT确保对某类错误进行检查的另一种情况是空检查。JIT与运行时协调完成这一点，其中JIT确保适当的指令到位以引发硬件异常，并且运行时然后将这些故障转换为.NET异常（例如：这里）。但有时指令仅用于空检查而不是还实现其他必要的功能，并且只要所需的空检查由于某些指令而发生，就可以移除不必要的重复指令。考虑以下代码：

    private (int i, int j) _value;

[Benchmark]
public int NullCheck() => _value.j++;

    As a runnable benchmark, this does too little work to accurately measure with Benchmark.NET, but it’s a great way to see what assembly code is generated. With .NET Core 3.1, this method results in this assembly:
    作为一个可运行的基准测试，这做的工作太少，无法用Benchmark.NET精确地测量，但它是查看生成了哪些汇编代码的好方法。对于.NET Core 3.1，此方法将生成以下程序集： 

    ; Program.NullCheck()
       nop       dword ptr [rax+rax]
       cmp       [rcx],ecx
       add       rcx,8
       add       rcx,4
       mov       eax,[rcx]
       lea       edx,[rax+1]
       mov       [rcx],edx
       ret
; Total bytes of code 23

    That cmp [rcx],ecx instruction is performing a null check on this as part of calculating the address of j. Then the mov eax,[rcx] instruction is performing another null check as part of dereferencing j‘s location. That first null check is thus not actually necessary, with the instruction not providing any other benefits. So, thanks to PRs like dotnet/runtime#1735 and dotnet/runtime#32641, such duplication is recognized by the JIT in many more cases than before, and for .NET 5 we now end up with:
    该 cmp [rcx],ecx 指令正在对 this 执行空校验，作为计算 j 地址的一部分。然后， mov eax,[rcx] 指令执行另一个空校验，作为解引用 j 的位置的一部分。因此，第一空校验实际上不是必需的，其中指令不提供任何其他益处。因此，多亏了像dotnet/runtime#1735和dotnet/runtime#32641这样的PR，JIT在比以前更多的情况下识别这种重复，对于.NET 5，我们现在结束了：

    ; Program.NullCheck()
       add       rcx,0C
       mov       eax,[rcx]
       lea       edx,[rax+1]
       mov       [rcx],edx
       ret
; Total bytes of code 12

    Covariance is another case where the JIT needs to inject checks to ensure that a developer can’t accidentally break type or memory safety. Consider code like:
    协方差是JIT需要注入检查以确保开发人员不会意外破坏类型或内存安全的另一种情况。考虑如下代码： 

    class A { }
class B { }
object[] arr = ...;
arr[0] = new A();

    Is this code valid? It depends. Arrays in .NET are “covariant”, which means I can pass around an array DerivedType[] as a BaseType[], where DerivedType derives from BaseType. That means in this example, the arr could have been constructed as new A[1] or new object[1] or new B[1]. This code should run fine with the first two, but if the arr is actually a B[], trying to store an A instance into it must fail; otherwise, code that’s using the array as a B[] could try to use B[0] as a B and things could go badly quickly. So, the runtime needs to protect against this by doing covariance checking, which really means when a reference type instance is stored into an array, the runtime needs to check that the assigned type is in fact compatible with the concrete type of the array. With dotnet/runtime#189, the JIT is now able to eliminate more covariance checks, specifically in the case where the element type of the array is sealed, like string. As a result of this, a microbenchmark like this now runs faster:
    这个代码有效吗？看情况.NET中的数组是“协变”的，这意味着我可以将数组 DerivedType[] 作为 BaseType[] 传递，其中 DerivedType 从 BaseType 派生。这意味着在这个例子中， arr 可以被构造为 new A[1] 或 new object[1] 或 new B[1] 。这段代码在前两个实例中应该可以正常运行，但是如果 arr 实际上是 B[] ，那么尝试将 A 实例存储到其中一定会失败;否则，使用数组作为 B[] 的代码可能会尝试使用 B[0] 作为 B ，结果可能会很快变得糟糕。因此，运行时需要通过协方差检查来防止这种情况，这实际上意味着当引用类型实例存储到数组中时，运行时需要检查分配的类型是否与数组的具体类型兼容。使用dotnet/runtime#189，JIT现在能够消除更多的协方差检查，特别是在数组的元素类型被密封的情况下，如 string 。因此，像这样的微基准测试现在运行得更快：

    private string[] _array = new string[1000];

[Benchmark]
public void CovariantChecking()
{
    string[] array = _array;
    for (int i = 0; i < array.Length; i++)
        array[i] = "default";
}
    Method 方法 Runtime 运行时 Mean 意味 Ratio 比 Code Size 代码大小
    CovariantChecking 协变量检查 .NET FW 4.8 2.121 us 2.121us 1.00 57 B
    CovariantChecking 协变量检查 .NET Core 3.1 2.122 us 2.122美元 1.00 57 B
    CovariantChecking 协变量检查 .NET 5.0 1.666 us 1.666美元 0.79 52 B

    Related to this are type checks. I mentioned earlier that Span<T> solved a bunch of problems but also introduced new patterns that then drove improvements in other areas of the system; that goes as well for the implementation of Span<T> itself. Span<T>‘s constructor does a covariance check that requires a T[] to actually be a T[] and not a U[] where U derives from T, e.g. this program:
    与此相关的是类型检查。我之前提到过 Span<T> 解决了一系列问题，但也引入了新的模式，然后推动了系统的其他领域的改进; Span<T> 本身也是如此。 Span<T> 的构造函数进行协方差检查，要求 T[] 实际上是 T[] 而不是 U[] ，其中 U 源自 T ，例如：这个程序：

    using System;

    这个异常源于 Span<T> 的构造函数中的这个检查：

    if (!typeof(T).IsValueType && array.GetType() != typeof(T[]))
    ThrowHelper.ThrowArrayTypeMismatchException();

    PR dotnet/runtime#32790 optimized just such a array.GetType() != typeof(T[]) check when T is sealed, while dotnet/runtime#1157 recognizes the typeof(T).IsValueType pattern and replaces it with a constant value (PR dotnet/runtime#1195 does the same for typeof(T1).IsAssignableFrom(typeof(T2))). The net effect of that is huge improvement on a microbenchmark like this:

    As another example, in the GC discussion earlier I called out a bunch of benefits we’ve experienced from porting native runtime code to be managed C# code. One that I didn’t mention then but will now is that it’s resulted in us making other improvements in the system that addressed key blockers to such porting but that then also serve to improve many other cases. A good example of that is dotnet/runtime#38229. When we first moved the native array sorting implementation to managed, we inadvertently incurred a regression for floating-point values, a regression that was helpfully spotted by @nietras and which was subsequently fixed in dotnet/runtime#37941. The regression was due to the native implementation employing a special optimization that we were missing in the managed port (for floating-point arrays, moving all NaN values to the beginning of the array such that subsequent comparison operations could ignore the possibility of NaNs), and we successfully brought that over. The problem, however, was expressing this in a way that didn’t result in tons of code duplication: the native implementation used templates, and the managed implementation used generics, but a limitation in inlining with generics made it such that helpers introduced to avoid lots of code duplication were causing non-inlineable method calls on every comparison employed in the sort. PR dotnet/runtime#38229 addressed that by enabling the JIT to inline shared generic code within the same type. Consider this microbenchmark:
    作为另一个例子，在前面的GC讨论中，我列举了将本地运行时代码移植为托管C#代码所带来的一系列好处。我当时没有提到但现在会提到的一点是，它导致我们在系统中做出了其他改进，解决了这种移植的关键障碍，但这也有助于改善许多其他情况。一个很好的例子是dotnet/runtime#38229。当我们第一次将原生数组排序实现迁移到托管时，我们无意中导致了浮点值的回归，这个回归被@nietras很有帮助地发现，随后在dotnet/runtime#37941中修复。回归是由于本地实现采用了一种特殊的优化，我们在托管端口中缺少了这种优化（对于浮点数组，将所有NaN值移动到数组的开头，以便后续的比较操作可以忽略NaN的可能性），我们成功地解决了这一点。 然而，问题在于，以一种不会导致大量代码重复的方式表达这一点：本机实现使用模板，而托管实现使用泛型，但是与泛型内联的限制使得引入以避免大量代码重复的帮助器在排序中使用的每个比较上导致不可内联的方法调用。PR dotnet/runtime#38229通过启用JIT在相同类型内内联共享泛型代码来解决这个问题。 看看这个微基准：

    private C c1 = new C() { Value = 1 }, c2 = new C() { Value = 2 }, c3 = new C() { Value = 3 };

[Benchmark]
public int Compare() => Comparer<C>.Smallest(c1, c2, c3);

class Comparer<T> where T : IComparable<T>
{
    public static int Smallest(T t1, T t2, T t3) =>
        Compare(t1, t2) <= 0 ?
            (Compare(t1, t3) <= 0 ? 0 : 2) :
            (Compare(t2, t3) <= 0 ? 1 : 2);

    [MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining)]
    private static int Compare(T t1, T t2) => t1.CompareTo(t2);
}

class C : IComparable<C>
{
    public int Value;
    public int CompareTo(C other) => other is null ? 1 : Value.CompareTo(other.Value);
}

    The Smallest method is comparing the three supplied values and returning the index of the smallest. It is a method on a generic type, and it’s calling to another method on that same type, which is in turn making calls out to methods on an instance of the generic type parameter. As the benchmark is using C as the generic type, and as C is a reference type, the JIT will not specialize the code for this method specifically for C, and will instead use a “shared” implementation it generates to be used for all reference types. In order for the Compare method to then call out to the correct interface implementation of CompareTo, that shared generic implementation employs a dictionary that maps from the generic type to the right target. In previous versions of .NET, methods containing those generic dictionary lookups were not inlineable, which means that this Smallest method can’t inline the three calls it makes to Compare, even though Compare is attributed as MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining. The aforementioned PR removed that limitation, resulting in a very measurable speedup on this example (and making the array sorting regression fix feasible):
    Smallest 方法比较三个提供的值并返回最小值的索引。它是泛型类型上的一个方法，它调用同一类型上的另一个方法，然后调用泛型类型参数实例上的方法。由于基准测试使用 C 作为泛型类型，并且 C 是引用类型，JIT不会专门针对 C 为此方法的代码，而是使用它生成的“共享”实现来用于所有引用类型。为了让 Compare 方法调用 CompareTo 的正确接口实现，共享泛型实现采用了一个字典，该字典从泛型类型映射到正确的目标。在以前的.NET版本中，包含这些泛型字典查找的方法是不可内联的，这意味着这个 Smallest 方法不能内联它对 Compare 的三次调用，即使 Compare 被属性为 MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining 。 前面提到的PR消除了这个限制，从而在这个例子中产生了非常可测量的加速（并使数组排序回归修复可行）：

    Method 方法 Runtime 运行时 Mean 意味 Ratio 比
    Compare 比较 .NET FW 4.8 8.632 ns 8.632纳秒 1.00
    Compare 比较 .NET Core 3.1 9.259 ns 9.259纳秒 1.07
    Compare 比较 .NET 5.0 5.282 ns 5.282纳秒 0.61

    Most of the cited improvements here have focused on throughput, with the JIT producing code that executes more quickly, and that faster code is often (though not always) smaller. Folks working on the JIT actually pay a lot of attention to code size, in many cases using it as a primary metric for whether a change is beneficial or not. Smaller code is not always faster code (instructions can be the same size but have very different cost profiles), but at a high level it’s a reasonable metric, and smaller code does have direct benefits, such as less impact on instruction caches, less code to load, etc. In some cases, changes are focused entirely on reducing code size, such as in cases where unnecessary duplication occurs. Consider this simple benchmark:
    这里提到的大多数改进都集中在吞吐量上，JIT生成的代码执行得更快，而且更快的代码通常（虽然不总是）更小。在JIT中工作的人实际上非常关注代码大小，在许多情况下，他们将其作为一个改变是否有益的主要指标。较小的代码并不总是更快的代码（指令可以是相同的大小，但具有非常不同的成本分布），但在高水平上这是一个合理的度量，并且较小的代码确实具有直接的好处，例如对指令缓存的影响较小，加载的代码较少等。在某些情况下，更改完全集中在减少代码大小上，例如在发生不必要的重复的情况下。考虑这个简单的基准测试： 

    private int _offset = 0;

[Benchmark]
public int ThrowHelpers()
{
    var arr = new int[10];
    var s0 = new Span<int>(arr, _offset, 1);
    var s1 = new Span<int>(arr, _offset + 1, 1);
    var s2 = new Span<int>(arr, _offset + 2, 1);
    var s3 = new Span<int>(arr, _offset + 3, 1);
    var s4 = new Span<int>(arr, _offset + 4, 1);
    var s5 = new Span<int>(arr, _offset + 5, 1);
    return s0[0] + s1[0] + s2[0] + s3[0] + s4[0] + s5[0];
}

    The Span<T> constructor does argument validation, which, when T is a value type, results in there being two call sites to a method on the ThrowHelper class, one that throws for a failed null check on the input array and one that throws when offset and count are out of range (ThrowHelper contains non-inlinable methods like ThrowArgumentNullException, which contains the actual throw and avoids the associated code size at every call site; the JIT currently isn’t capable of “outlining”, the opposite of “inlining”, so it needs to be done manually in cases where it matters). In the above example, we’re creating six spans, which means six calls to the Span<T> constructor, all of which will be inlined. The JIT can see that the array is non-null, so it can eliminate the null check and the ThrowArgumentNullException from inlined code, but it doesn’t know whether the offset and count are in range, so it needs to retain the range check and the call site for the ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException method. In .NET Core 3.1, that results in code like the following being generated for this ThrowHelpers method:
    Span<T> 构造函数执行参数验证，当 T 是值类型时，会导致对 ThrowHelper 类上的方法有两个调用站点，一个在输入数组上抛出失败的空检查，另一个在offset和count超出范围时抛出（ ThrowHelper 包含不可内联的方法，如 ThrowArgumentNullException ，它包含实际的 throw ，避免了每个调用站点的相关代码大小; JIT目前还不能“大纲”，这与“内联”相反，因此在重要的情况下需要手动完成）。在上面的例子中，我们创建了六个span，这意味着对 Span<T> 构造函数的六次调用，所有这些都将内联。JIT可以看到数组是非空的，所以它可以从内联代码中消除空校验和 ThrowArgumentNullException ，但它不知道偏移量和计数是否在范围内，所以它需要保留范围校验和 ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException 方法的调用位置。.NET Core 3.1，这导致为这个 ThrowHelpers 方法生成如下代码：

    M00_L00:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3
M00_L01:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3
M00_L02:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3
M00_L03:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3
M00_L04:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3
M00_L05:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3

    In .NET 5, thanks to dotnet/coreclr#27113, the JIT is able to recognize this duplication, and instead of all six call sites, it’ll end up consolidating them into just one:
    在.NET 5中，多亏了dotnet/coreclr#27113，JIT能够识别这种重复，而不是所有六个调用站点，它最终将它们合并为一个：

    M00_L00:
       call      System.ThrowHelper.ThrowArgumentOutOfRangeException()
       int       3

    with all failed checks jumping to this shared location rather than each having its own copy.
    所有失败的检查都跳转到这个共享位置，而不是每个检查都具有其自己的副本。

    Method 方法 Runtime 运行时 Code Size 代码大小
    ThrowHelpers .NET FW 4.8 424 B B
    ThrowHelpers .NET Core 3.1 252 B
    ThrowHelpers .NET 5.0 222 B

    These are just some of the myriad of improvements that have gone into the JIT in .NET 5. There are many more. dotnet/runtime#32368 causes the JIT to see an array’s length as unsigned, which results in it being able to use better instructions for some mathematical operations (e.g. division) performed on the length. dotnet/coreclr#25458 enables the JIT to use faster 0-based comparisons for some unsigned integer operations, e.g. using the equivalent of a != 0 when the developer actually wrote a >= 1. dotnet/runtime#1378 allows the JIT to recognize “constantString”.Length as a constant value. dotnet/runtime#26740 reduces the size of ReadyToRun images by removing nop padding. dotnet/runtime#330234 optimizes the instructions generated when performing x * 2 when x is a float or double, using an add instead of a multiply. dotnet/runtime#27060 improves the code generated for the Math.FusedMultiplyAdd intrinsic. dotnet/runtime#27384 makes volatile operations cheaper on ARM64 by using better fence instructions than were previously used, and dotnet/runtime#38179 performs a peephole optimization on ARM64 to remove a bunch of redundant mov instructions. And on and on.
    这些只是.NET 5中JIT的无数改进中的一部分。还有很多。dotnet/runtime#32368使得JIT将数组的长度视为无符号，这使得它能够使用更好的指令来进行一些数学运算（例如：分）在长度上执行。dotnet/coreclr#25458使JIT能够对一些无符号整数运算使用更快的基于0的比较，例如当开发人员实际编写 a >= 1 时，使用的是 a != 0 。dotnet/runtime#1378允许JIT将“constantString”.Length识别为常数值。dotnet/runtime#26740通过删除 nop 填充来减小ReadyToRun映像的大小。dotnet/runtime#330234优化了当 x 是 float 或 double 时执行 x * 2 时生成的指令，使用加法而不是乘法。dotnet/runtime#27060改进了为 Math.FusedMultiplyAdd 内在生成的代码。 dotnet/runtime#27384通过使用比以前使用的更好的围栏指令，使易失性操作在ARM 64上更便宜，dotnet/runtime#38179在ARM 64上执行窥视孔优化，以删除一堆冗余的 mov 指令。一个又一个。

    There are also some significant changes in the JIT that are disabled by default, with the goal of getting real-world feedback on them and being able to enable them by default post-.NET 5. For example, dotnet/runtime#32969 provides an initial implementation of “On Stack Replacement” (OSR). I mentioned tiered compilation earlier, which enables the JIT to first generate minimally-optimized code for a method, and then subsequently recompile a method with much more optimization when that method is shown to be important. This enables faster start-up time by allowing code to get going more quickly and only upgrading impactful methods once things are running. However, tiered compilation relies on being able to replace an implementation, and the next time it’s called, the new one will be invoked. But what about long-running methods? Tiered compilation is disabled by default for methods that contain loops (or, more specifically, backward branches) because they could end up running for a long time such that the replacement may not be used in a timely manner. OSR enables methods to be updated while their code is executing, while they’re “on stack”; lots of great details are in the design document included in that PR (also related to tiered compilation, dotnet/runtime#1457 improves the call-counting mechanism by which tiered compilation decides which methods should be recompiled, and when). You can experiment with OSR by setting both the COMPlus_TC_QuickJitForLoops and COMPlus_TC_OnStackReplacement environment variables to 1. As another example, dotnet/runtime#1180 improves the generated code quality for code inside try blocks, enabling the JIT to keep values in registers where it previously couldn’t. You can experiment with this by setting the COMPlus_EnableEHWriteThr environment variable to 1.
    JIT中还有一些重要的更改在默认情况下是禁用的，目的是获得对它们的真实反馈，并能够在.NET 5之后默认启用它们。例如，dotnet/runtime#32969提供了“堆栈替换”（OSR）的初始实现。我前面提到过分层编译，它使JIT能够首先为一个方法生成最低限度优化的代码，然后在证明该方法重要时重新编译一个方法，并进行更多优化。这允许代码更快地运行，并且在运行后只升级有影响力的方法，从而加快了启动时间。然而，分层编译依赖于能够替换实现，下次调用它时，将调用新的实现。但长期运行的方法呢？ 默认情况下，对于包含循环（或者更具体地说，是反向分支）的方法，分层编译是禁用的，因为它们最终可能会运行很长时间，从而可能无法及时使用替换。OSR允许方法在代码执行时被更新，而它们是“在堆栈上”;许多重要的细节都在PR中包含的设计文档中（也与分层编译相关，dotnet/runtime#1457改进了调用计数机制，分层编译通过该机制决定哪些方法应该被重新编译，以及何时被重新编译）。您可以通过将 COMPlus_TC_QuickJitForLoops 和 COMPlus_TC_OnStackReplacement 环境变量设置为 1 来试验OSR。作为另一个例子，dotnet/runtime#1180提高了try块内代码生成的代码质量，使JIT能够将值保存在寄存器中，以前不能保存。您可以通过将 COMPlus_EnableEHWriteThr 环境变量设置为 1 来进行实验。

    There are also a bunch of pending pull requests to the JIT that haven’t yet been merged but that very well could be before .NET 5 is released (in addition to, I expect, many more that haven’t been put up yet but will before .NET 5 ships in a few months). For example, dotnet/runtime#32716 enables the JIT to replace some branching comparison like a == 42 ? 3 : 2 with branchless implementations, which can help with performance when the hardware isn’t able to correctly predict which branch would be taken. Or dotnet/runtime#37226, which enables the JIT to take a pattern like "hello"[0] and replace it with just h; while generally a developer doesn’t write such code, this can help when inlining is involved, with a constant string passed into a method that gets inlined and that indexes into a constant location (generally after a length check, which, thanks to dotnet/runtime#1378, can also become a const). Or dotnet/runtime#1224, which improves the code generation for the Bmi2.MultiplyNoFlags intrinsic. Or dotnet/runtime#37836, which turns BitOperations.PopCount into an intrinsic in a manner that enables the JIT to recognize when it’s called with a constant argument and replace the whole operation with a precomputed constant. Or dotnet/runtime#37254, which removes null checks emitted when working with const strings. Or dotnet/runtime#32000 from @damageboy, which optimizes double negations.
    还有一堆到JIT的未决拉取请求尚未合并，但很可能在.NET 5发布之前就已经合并（此外，我预计，还有更多的请求还没有被提交，但将在.NET 5发布几个月前）。例如，dotnet/runtime#32716使JIT能够用无分支实现来替换一些分支比较（如 a == 42 ? 3 : 2 ），这可以在硬件无法正确预测将采取哪个分支时帮助提高性能。或者dotnet/runtime#37226，它使JIT能够采用类似 "hello"[0] 的模式，并将其替换为 h ;虽然开发人员通常不会编写这样的代码，但当涉及内联时，这会有所帮助，将常量字符串传递到方法中，该方法被内联并索引到常量位置（通常在长度检查之后，由于dotnet/runtime#1378，常量位置也可以变成常量）。或者dotnet/runtime#1224，它改进了 Bmi2.MultiplyNoFlags 内在代码的生成。 或者dotnet/runtime#37836，它将 BitOperations.PopCount 转换为一个内在函数，使得JIT能够识别何时用常量参数调用它，并将整个操作替换为预先计算的常量。或者dotnet/runtime#37254，它删除了在使用const字符串时发出的null检查。或者来自@damageboy的dotnet/runtime#32000，它优化了双重否定。

    Intrinsics 内部函数

    In .NET Core 3.0, over a thousand new hardware intrinsics methods were added and recognized by the JIT to enable C# code to directly target instruction sets like SSE4 and AVX2 (see the docs). These were then used to great benefit in a bunch of APIs in the core libraries. However, the intrinsics were limited to x86/x64 architectures. In .NET 5, a ton of effort has gone into adding thousands more, specific to ARM64, thanks to multiple contributors, and in particular @TamarChristinaArm from Arm Holdings. And as with their x86/x64 counterparts, these intrinsics have been put to good use inside core library functionality. For example, the BitOperations.PopCount() method was previously optimized to use the x86 POPCNT intrinsic, and for .NET 5, dotnet/runtime#35636 augments it to also be able to use the ARM VCNT or ARM64 CNT equivalent. Similarly, dotnet/runtime#34486 modified BitOperations.LeadingZeroCount, TrailingZeroCount, and Log2 to utilize the corresponding instrincs. And at a higher level, dotnet/runtime#33749 from @Gnbrkm41 augments multiple methods in BitArray to use ARM64 intrinsics to go along with the previously added support for SSE2 and AVX2. Lots of work has gone into ensuring that the Vector APIs perform well on ARM64, too, such as with dotnet/runtime#37139 and dotnet/runtime#36156.
    在.NET Core 3.0中，添加了一千多个新的硬件内部函数方法，并被JIT识别，使C#代码能够直接针对SSE 4和AVX 2等指令集（参见文档）。然后，这些被用于核心库中的一堆API中，从中受益匪浅。然而，intrinsic仅限于x86/x64架构。在.NET 5中，由于多个贡献者，特别是Arm Holdings的@TamarChristinaArm，已经付出了大量的努力来增加数千个特定于ARM 64的内容。与x86/x64的对应部分一样，这些内在函数在核心库功能中得到了很好的利用。例如， BitOperations.PopCount() 方法先前被优化为使用x86 POPCNT固有，而对于.NET 5，dotnet/runtime#35636将其增强为也能够使用ARM VCNT或ARM 64 CNT等效物。类似地，dotnet/runtime#34486修改了 BitOperations.LeadingZeroCount 、 TrailingZeroCount 和 Log2 以使用相应的指令。 在更高的层次上，来自@Gnbrkm41的dotnet/runtime#33749增加了 BitArray 中的多个方法，以使用ARM 64 intrinsic来沿着之前添加的对SSE 2和AVX 2的支持。我们已经做了很多工作来确保 Vector API在ARM 64上也能很好地运行，比如dotnet/runtime#37139和dotnet/runtime#36156。

    Beyond ARM64, additional work has been done to vectorize more operations. For example, @Gnbrkm41 also submitted dotnet/runtime#31993, which utilized ROUNDPS/ROUNDPD on x64 and FRINPT/FRINTM on ARM64 to improve the code generated for the new Vector.Ceiling and Vector.Floor methods. And BitOperations (which is a relatively low-level type implemented for most operations as a 1:1 wrapper around the most appropriate hardware intrinsics) was not only improved in dotnet/runtime#35650 from @saucecontrol but also had its usage in Corelib improved to be more efficient.
    除了ARM 64之外，还做了更多的工作来实现更多的操作。例如，@Gnbrkm41还提交了dotnet/runtime#31993，它在x64上使用了ROUNDPS/ROUNDPD，在ARM 64上使用了FRINPT/FRINTM来改进为新的 Vector.Ceiling 和 Vector.Floor 方法生成的代码。 BitOperations （这是一个相对较低级别的类型，用于大多数操作，作为一个围绕最合适的硬件内在函数的1：1包装器实现）不仅在@saucecontrol的dotnet/runtime#35650中得到了改进，而且在Corelib中的使用也得到了改进，以更高效。

    Finally, a whole slew of changes went into the JIT to better handle hardware intrinsics and vectorization in general, such as dotnet/runtime#35421, dotnet/runtime#31834, dotnet/runtime#1280, dotnet/runtime#35857, dotnet/runtime#36267, and dotnet/runtime#35525.
    最后，JIT进行了一系列的更改，以更好地处理硬件固有和一般的向量化，例如dotnet/runtime#35421、dotnet/runtime#31834、dotnet/runtime#1280、dotnet/runtime#35857、dotnet/runtime#36267和dotnet/runtime#35525。

    Runtime Helpers 运行时帮助程序

    The GC and JIT represent large portions of the runtime, but there still remains significant portions of functionality in the runtime outside of these components, and those have similarly seen improvements.
    GC和JIT代表了运行时的很大一部分，但是运行时中仍然有重要的功能部分在这些组件之外，而且这些功能也得到了类似的改进。

    It’s interesting to note that the JIT doesn’t generate code from scratch for everything. There are many places where pre-existing helper functions are invoked by the JIT, with the runtime supplying those helpers, and improvements to those helpers can have meaningful impact on programs. dotnet/runtime#23548 is a great example. In libraries like System.Linq, we’ve shied away from adding additional type checks for covariant interfaces because of significantly higher overhead for them versus for normal interfaces. dotnet/runtime#23548 (subsequently tweaked in dotnet/runtime#34427) essentially adds a cache, such that the cost of these casts are amortized and end up being much faster overall. This is evident from a simple microbenchmark:
    值得注意的是，JIT并不是从零开始生成所有代码。在许多地方，JIT调用预先存在的帮助函数，运行时提供这些帮助函数，对这些帮助函数的改进可以对程序产生有意义的影响。dotnet/runtime#23548就是一个很好的例子。在像 System.Linq 这样的库中，我们避免为协变接口添加额外的类型检查，因为它们的开销比普通接口要高得多。dotnet/runtime#23548（随后在dotnet/runtime#34427中进行了调整）本质上增加了一个缓存，这样这些类型转换的成本就可以分摊，最终总体上更快。从一个简单的微基准测试中可以看出这一点：

    private List<string> _list = new List<string>();

    Another set of impactful changes came in dotnet/runtime#32270 (with JIT support in dotnet/runtime#31957). In the past, generic methods maintained just a few dedicated dictionary slots that could be used for fast lookup of the types associated with the generic method; once those slots were exhausted, it fell back to a slower lookup table. The need for this limitation no longer exists, and these changes enabled fast lookup slots to be used for all generic lookups.
    另一组有影响力的变化来自dotnet/runtime#32270（dotnet/runtime#31957中有JIT支持）。在过去，泛型方法只维护几个专用的字典槽，这些槽可以用于快速查找与泛型方法相关联的类型;一旦这些槽用完，它就回到较慢的查找表。不再需要这种限制，并且这些变化使快速查找槽能够用于所有通用查找。

    [Benchmark]
public void GenericDictionaries()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 14; i++)
        GenericMethod<string>(i);

[MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.NoInlining)]

{
    switch (level)
    {
        case 0: return typeof(T);

        case 5: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>);
        case 6: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>);
        case 7: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>);
        case 8: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>>);
        case 9: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>>>);
        case 10: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>>>>);
        case 11: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>>>>>);
        case 12: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>>>>>>);
        default: return typeof(List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<List<T>>>>>>>>>>>>>);
    }
}

    Text Processing 文本处理

    Text-based processing is the bread-and-butter of many applications, and a lot of effort in every release goes into improving the fundamental building blocks on top of which everything else is built. Such changes extend from microoptimizations in helpers processing individual characters all the way up to overhauls of entire text-processing libraries.
    基于文本的处理是许多应用程序的基础，在每个版本中，大量的工作都用于改进基本的构建块，而其他所有内容都是在此基础上构建的。这些变化从处理单个字符的助手中的微优化一直延伸到整个文本处理库的大修。

    System.Char received some nice improvements in .NET 5. For example, dotnet/coreclr#26848 improved the performance of char.IsWhiteSpace by tweaking the implementation to require fewer instructions and less branching. Improvements to char.IsWhiteSpace then manifest in a bunch of other methods that rely on it, like string.IsEmptyOrWhiteSpace and Trim:
    System.Char 在.NET 5中获得了一些不错的改进。例如，dotnet/coreclr#26848通过调整实现，使其需要更少的指令和更少的分支来提高 char.IsWhiteSpace 的性能。对 char.IsWhiteSpace 的改进体现在其他依赖它的方法中，比如 string.IsEmptyOrWhiteSpace 和 Trim ：

    [Benchmark]

    Another nice example, dotnet/runtime#35194 improved the performance of char.ToUpperInvariant and char.ToLowerInvariant by improving the inlineability of various methods, streamlining the call paths from the public APIs down to the core functionality, and further tweaking the implementation to ensure the JIT was generating the best code.
    另一个很好的例子，dotnet/runtime#35194通过改进各种方法的内联性，简化了从公共API到核心功能的调用路径，并进一步调整实现以确保JIT生成最好的代码，从而提高了 char.ToUpperInvariant 和 char.ToLowerInvariant 的性能。

    [Benchmark]
[Arguments("It's exciting to see great performance!")]

{
    int sum = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < s.Length; i++)
        sum += char.ToUpperInvariant(s[i]);

    return sum;

    Going beyond single characters, in practically every release of .NET Core, we’ve worked to push the envelope for how fast we can make the existing formatting APIs. This release is no different. And even though previous releases saw significant wins, this one moves the bar further.
    除了单个字符之外，几乎在.NET Core的每一个版本中，我们都在努力提高现有格式化API的速度。这次发布也没有什么不同。即使以前的版本看到了重大的胜利，这一个移动的酒吧更进一步。

    Int32.ToString() 是一个非常常见的操作，而且速度非常重要。@ts2do的dotnet/runtime#32528通过为该方法使用的关键格式化例程添加可内联的快速路径，并通过简化各种公共API访问这些例程所采用的路径，使其更快。其他原始 ToString 操作也得到了改进。例如，dotnet/runtime#27056简化了一些代码路径，以使从公共API到实际上将位写入内存的点的操作更少。

    In a similar vein, in previous releases we did some fairly heavy optimizations on DateTime and DateTimeOffset, but those improvements were primarily focused on how quickly we could convert the day/month/year/etc. data into the right characters or bytes and write them to the destination.     Of course, low-level processing is all well and good, but applications these days spend a lot of time doing higher-level operations like encoding of data in a particular format, such as UTF8. Previous .NET Core releases saw Encoding.UTF8 optimized, but in .NET 5 it’s still improved further. dotnet/runtime#27268 optimizes it more, in particular for smaller inputs, by taking better advantage of stack allocation and improvements made in JIT devirtualization (where the JIT is able to avoid virtual dispatch due to being able to discover the actual concrete type of the instance it’s working with).

    Regular Expressions 正则表达式

    A very specific but extremely common form of parsing is via regular expressions. Back in early April, I shared a detailed blog post about some of the myriad of performance improvements that have gone into .NET 5 for System.Text.RegularExpressions. I’m not going to rehash all of that here, but I would encourage you to read it if haven’t already, as it represents significant advancements in the library. However, I also noted in that post that we would continue to improve Regex, and we have, in particular adding in more support for special but common cases.
    一种非常具体但非常常见的解析形式是通过正则表达式。早在4月初，我分享了一篇详细的博客文章，介绍了.NET 5 for System.Text.RegularExpressions的一些性能改进。我不打算在这里重复所有这些，但我鼓励你阅读它，如果还没有，因为它代表了图书馆的重大进步。然而，我在那篇文章中也指出，我们将继续改进 Regex ，我们已经，特别是增加了对特殊但常见的情况的更多支持。

    One such improvement was in newline handling when specifying RegexOptions.Multiline, which changes the meaning of the ^ and $ anchors to match at the beginning and end of any line rather than just the beginning and end of the whole input string. We previously didn’t do any special handling of beginning-of-line anchors (^ when Multiline is specified), which meant that as part of the FindFirstChar operation (see the aforementioned blog post for background on what that refers to), we wouldn’t skip ahead as much as we otherwise could. dotnet/runtime#34566 taught FindFirstChar how to use a vectorized IndexOf to jump ahead to the next relevant location. The impact of that is highlighted in this benchmark, which is processing the text of “Romeo and Juliet” as downloaded from Project Gutenberg:
    一个这样的改进是在指定 RegexOptions.Multiline 时的换行符处理中，它改变了 ^ 和 $ 锚点的含义，以匹配任何行的开始和结束，而不仅仅是整个输入字符串的开始和结束。我们之前没有对行开头锚点进行任何特殊处理（当指定 Multiline 时为 ^ ），这意味着作为 FindFirstChar 操作的一部分（参见前面提到的博客文章，了解它所指的内容），我们不会像其他方式那样跳过。dotnet/runtime#34566教导 FindFirstChar 如何使用矢量化的 IndexOf 跳转到下一个相关位置。这个基准测试强调了这一影响，它正在处理从古滕贝格项目下载的“罗密欧与朱丽叶”的文本：

    One of my favorite recent optimizations, though, was dotnet/runtime#35824 (which was then augmented further in dotnet/runtime#35936). The change recognizes that, for a regex beginning with an atomic loop (one explicitly written or more commonly one upgraded to being atomic by automatic analysis of the expression), we can update the next starting position in the scan loop (again, see the blog post for details) based on where the loop ended rather than on where it started. For many inputs, this can provide a big reduction in overhead. Using the benchmark and data from https://github.com/mariomka/regex-benchmark:
    不过，我最近最喜欢的优化之一是dotnet/runtime#35824（后来在dotnet/runtime#35936中得到了进一步的扩展）。这个变化认识到，对于以原子循环开始的正则表达式（一个显式编写的，或者更常见的是通过表达式的自动分析升级为原子循环），我们可以根据循环结束的位置而不是开始的位置来更新扫描循环中的下一个起始位置（再次，请参阅博客文章了解详细信息）。对于许多输入，这可以大大减少开销。使用来自https://github.com/mariomka/regex-benchmark的基准和数据：

    Finally, not all focus was on the raw throughput of actually executing regular expressions. One of the ways developers can get the best throughput with Regex is by specifying RegexOptions.Compiled, which uses Reflection Emit to at runtime generate IL, which in turn needs to be JIT compiled. Depending on the expressions employed, Regex may spit out a fair amount of IL, which then can require a non-trivial amount of JIT processing to churn into assembly code. dotnet/runtime#35352 improved the JIT itself to help with this case, fixing some potentially quadratic-execution-time code paths the regex-generated IL was triggering. And dotnet/runtime#35321 tweaked the IL operations used by Regex engine to employ patterns much closer to what the C# compiler would emit, which is important because those same patterns are what the JIT is more tuned to optimize well. On some real-world workloads featuring several hundred complex regular expressions, these combined to reduce the time it took to JIT the expressions by upwards of 20%.
    最后，并不是所有的关注点都集中在实际执行正则表达式的原始吞吐量上。开发人员可以通过 Regex 获得最佳吞吐量的方法之一是指定 RegexOptions.Compiled ，它使用反射发射在运行时生成IL，然后需要JIT编译。根据使用的表达式， Regex 可能会吐出相当数量的IL，然后可能需要大量的JIT处理来转化成汇编代码。dotnet/runtime#35352改进了JIT本身以帮助解决这种情况，修复了regex生成的IL触发的一些潜在的二次执行时间代码路径。dotnet/runtime#35321调整了 Regex 引擎使用的IL操作，使其采用更接近C#编译器发出的模式，这一点很重要，因为这些相同的模式是JIT更优化的。 在一些具有数百个复杂正则表达式的实际工作负载中，这些组合可以将JIT表达式所需的时间减少20%以上。

    Threading and Async 线程和异步

    One of the biggest changes around asynchrony in .NET 5 is actually not enabled by default, but is another experiment to get feedback. The Async ValueTask Pooling in .NET 5 blog post explains this in much more detail, but essentially dotnet/coreclr#26310 introduced the ability for async ValueTask and async ValueTask<T> to implicitly cache and reuse the object created to represent an asynchronously completing operation, making the overhead of such methods amortized-allocation-free. The optimization is currently opt-in, meaning you need to set the DOTNET_SYSTEM_THREADING_POOLASYNCVALUETASKS environment variable to 1 in order to enable it. One of the difficulties with enabling this is for code that might be doing something more complex than just await SomeValueTaskReturningMethod(), as ValueTasks have more constraints than Tasks about how they can be used. To help with that, a new UseValueTasksCorrectly analyzer was released that will flag most such misuse.
    .NET 5中围绕异步的最大变化之一实际上是默认情况下不启用的，而是另一个获得反馈的实验。.NET 5博客文章中的Async ValueTask Pooling更详细地解释了这一点，但本质上dotnet/coreclr#26310引入了 async ValueTask 和 async ValueTask<T> 隐式缓存和重用为表示异步完成操作而创建的对象的能力，使得此类方法的开销被分摊-分配-free。优化目前是可选的，这意味着您需要将 DOTNET_SYSTEM_THREADING_POOLASYNCVALUETASKS 环境变量设置为 1 ，以便启用它。启用此功能的困难之一是代码可能要做比 await SomeValueTaskReturningMethod() 更复杂的事情，因为 ValueTasks 比 Task 有更多的约束，关于如何使用它们。为了帮助解决这一问题，发布了新的 UseValueTasksCorrectly 分析仪，该分析仪将标记大多数此类误用。

    [Benchmark]
public async Task ValueTaskCost()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 1_000; i++)
        await YieldOnce();
}

private static async ValueTask YieldOnce() => await Task.Yield();
