    ValueTaskCost .NET FW 4.8 1,635.6 us 1，635.6美元 1.00 294010 B
    ValueTaskCost .NET Core 3.1 842.7 us 842.7us 0.51 120184 B B行星120184
    ValueTaskCost .NET 5.0 812.3 us 812.3us 0.50 186 B B

    Some changes in the C# compiler accrue additional benefits to async methods in .NET 5 (in that the core libraries in .NET 5 are compiled with the newer compiler). Every async method has a “builder” that’s responsible for producing and completing the returned task, with the C# compiler generating code as part of an async method to use one. dotnet/roslyn#41253 from @benaadams avoids a struct copy generated as part of that code, which can help reduce overheads, in particular for async ValueTask<T> methods where the builder is relatively large (and grows as T grows). dotnet/roslyn#45262 also from @benaadams also tweaks the same generated code to play better with the JIT’s zero’ing improvements discussed previously.
    C#编译器中的一些更改为.NET 5中的异步方法带来了额外的好处（因为.NET 5中的核心库是用较新的编译器编译的）。每个async方法都有一个“builder”，负责生成和完成返回的任务，C#编译器生成代码作为async方法的一部分来使用。@benaadams的dotnet/roslyn#41253避免了作为代码的一部分生成的结构体副本，这有助于减少开销，特别是对于构建器相对较大（并且随着 T 的增长而增长）的 async ValueTask<T> 方法。同样来自@benaadams的dotnet/roslyn#45262也调整了相同生成的代码，以便更好地使用前面讨论的JIT的归零改进。

    There are also some improvements in specific APIs. dotnet/runtime#35575 was born out of some specific usage of Task.ContinueWith, where a continuation is used purely for the purposes of logging an exception in the “antecedent” Task continued from. The common case here is that the Task doesn’t fault, and this PR does a better job optimizing for that case.
    在特定的API中也有一些改进。dotnet/runtime#35575诞生于 Task.ContinueWith 的某些特定用法，其中continuation纯粹是为了记录“antecedent” Task continued from中的异常。这里的常见情况是 Task 没有故障，这个PR在这种情况下做了更好的优化工作。

    const int Iters = 1_000_000;

private AsyncTaskMethodBuilder[] tasks = new AsyncTaskMethodBuilder[Iters];

[IterationSetup]
public void Setup()
{
    Array.Clear(tasks, 0, tasks.Length);
    for (int i = 0; i < tasks.Length; i++)
        _ = tasks[i].Task;
}

[Benchmark(OperationsPerInvoke = Iters)]
public void Cancel()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < tasks.Length; i++)
    {
        tasks[i].Task.ContinueWith(_ => { }, CancellationToken.None, TaskContinuationOptions.OnlyOnFaulted | TaskContinuationOptions.ExecuteSynchronously, TaskScheduler.Default);
        tasks[i].SetResult();
    }
}
    Method 方法 Runtime 运行时 Mean 意味 Ratio 比 Allocated 分配
    Cancel 取消 .NET FW 4.8 239.2 ns 239.2纳秒 1.00 193 B B
    Cancel 取消 .NET Core 3.1 140.3 ns 0.59 192 B 192个B
    Cancel 取消 .NET 5.0 106.4 ns 0.44 112 B

    There were also tweaks to help with specific architectures. Because of the strong memory model employed by x86/x64 architectures, volatile essentially evaporates at JIT time when targeting x86/x64. That is not the case for ARM/ARM64, which have weaker memory models and where volatile results in fences being emitted by the JIT. dotnet/runtime#36697 removes several volatile accesses per work item queued to the ThreadPool, making the ThreadPool faster on ARM. dotnet/runtime#34225 hoisted a volatile access in ConcurrentDictionary out of a loop, which in turn improved throughput of some members on ConcurrentDictionary on ARM by as much as 30%. And dotnet/runtime#36976 removed volatile entirely from another ConcurrentDictionary field.
    还有一些调整，以帮助特定的架构。由于x86/x64架构所采用的强内存模型，当以x86/x64为目标时， volatile 基本上在JIT时间消失了。ARM/ARM 64的情况并非如此，它们具有较弱的内存模型，并且 volatile 导致JIT发出栅栏。dotnet/runtime#36697删除了排队到 ThreadPool 的每个工作项的几个易失性访问，使 ThreadPool 在ARM上更快。dotnet/runtime#34225将 ConcurrentDictionary 中的一个易失性访问提升到循环之外，这反过来又将ARM上 ConcurrentDictionary 上的一些成员的吞吐量提高了30%。dotnet/runtime#36976从另一个 ConcurrentDictionary 字段中完全删除了 volatile 。

    Collections 收藏

    Over the years, C# has gained a plethora of valuable features. Many of these features are focused on developers being able to more succinctly write code, with the language/compiler being responsible for all the boilerplate, such as with records in C# 9. However, a few features are focused less on productivity and more on performance, and such features are a great boon to the core libraries, which can often use them to make everyone’s program’s more efficient. dotnet/runtime#27195 from @benaadams is a good example of this. The PR improves Dictionary<TKey, TValue>, taking advantage of ref returns and ref locals, which were introduced in C# 7. Dictionary<TKey, TValue>‘s implementation is backed by an array of entries in the dictionary, and the dictionary has a core routine for looking up a key’s index in its entries array; that routine is then used from multiple functions, like the indexer, TryGetValue, ContainsKey, and so on. However, that sharing comes at a cost: by handing back the index and leaving it up to the caller to get the data from that slot as needed, the caller would need to re-index into the array, incurring a second bounds check. With ref returns, that shared routine could instead hand back a ref to the slot rather than the raw index, enabling the caller to avoid the second bounds check while also avoiding making a copy of the entire entry. The PR also included some low-level tuning of the generated assembly, reorganizing fields and the operations used to update those fields in a way that enabled the JIT to better tune the generated assembly.
    多年来，C#获得了大量有价值的特性。这些特性中的许多都集中在开发人员能够更简洁地编写代码上，语言/编译器负责所有的样板文件，例如C# 9中的记录。然而，一些特性不太关注生产力，而更多地关注性能，这些特性对核心库来说是一个巨大的布恩，核心库通常可以使用它们来提高每个人的程序的效率。来自@benaadams的dotnet/runtime#27195就是一个很好的例子。PR改进了 Dictionary<TKey, TValue> ，利用了C# 7中引入的ref返回和ref局部变量。 Dictionary<TKey, TValue> 的实现由字典中的条目数组支持，并且字典有一个核心例程，用于在其条目数组中查找键的索引;然后，该例程从多个函数中使用，例如索引器、 TryGetValue 、 ContainsKey 等等。 然而，这种共享是有代价的：通过移交索引并将其留给调用者以根据需要从该槽中获取数据，调用者将需要重新索引到数组中，从而引起第二次边界检查。使用ref返回，共享例程可以将ref返回到插槽而不是原始索引，从而使调用者能够避免第二次边界检查，同时也避免复制整个条目。PR还包括对生成的程序集的一些低级调优、重新组织字段和用于更新这些字段的操作，以使JIT能够更好地调优生成的程序集。

    Dictionary<TKey,TValue>‘s performance was improved further by several more PRs. Like many hash tables, Dictionary<TKey,TValue> is partitioned into “buckets”, each of which is essentially a linked list of entries (stored in an array, not with individual node objects per item). For a given key, a hashing function (TKey‘s GetHashCode or the supplied IComparer<T>‘s GetHashCode) is used to compute a hash code for the supplied key, and then that hash code is mapped deterministically to a bucket; once the bucket is found, the implementation then iterates through the chain of entries in that bucket looking for the target key. The implementation tries to keep the number of entries in each bucket small, growing and rebalancing as necessary to maintain that condition. As such, a large portion of the cost of a lookup is computing the hashcode-to-bucket mapping. In order to help maintain a good distribution across the buckets, especially when a less-than-ideal hash code generator is employed by the supplied TKey or comparer, the dictionary uses a prime number of buckets, and the bucket mapping is done by hashcode % numBuckets. But at the speeds important here, the division employed by the % operator is relatively expensive. Building on Daniel Lemire’s work, dotnet/coreclr#27299 from @benaadams and then dotnet/runtime#406 changed the use of % in 64-bit processes to instead use a couple of multiplications and shifts to achieve the same result but faster.
    Dictionary<TKey,TValue> 的性能通过多个PR得到进一步改善。像许多哈希表一样， Dictionary<TKey,TValue> 被划分为“buckets”，每个buckets本质上都是条目的链表（存储在数组中，而不是每个条目单独的节点对象）。对于给定的密钥，散列函数（ TKey 的 GetHashCode 或提供的 IComparer<T> 的 GetHashCode ）用于计算提供的密钥的散列码，然后该散列码被确定性地映射到桶;一旦找到桶，则该实现就迭代通过该桶中的条目链来寻找目标键。该实现试图保持每个桶中的条目数量较小，并根据需要增加并重新平衡以维持该条件。因此，查找的大部分成本是计算散列码到桶映射。 为了帮助保持桶之间的良好分布，特别是当提供的 TKey 或比较器采用不太理想的散列码生成器时，字典使用桶的素数，并且桶映射由 hashcode % numBuckets 完成。但在这里重要的速度下， % 操作员所采用的除法相对昂贵。基于丹尼尔Lemire的工作，来自@benaadams的dotnet/coreclr#27299和dotnet/runtime#406改变了64位进程中 % 的使用，改为使用几个乘法和移位来实现相同的结果，但速度更快。

    private Dictionary<int, int> _dictionary = Enumerable.Range(0, 10_000).ToDictionary(i => i);

    System.Collections.Immutable has also seen improvements in the release. dotnet/runtime#1183 is a one-line but impactful change from @hnrqbaggio to improve the performance of foreach‘ing over an ImmutableArray<T> by adding [MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining)] to ImmutableArray<T>‘s GetEnumerator method. We’re generally very cautious about sprinkling AggressiveInlining around: it can make microbenchmarks look really good, since it ends up eliminating the overhead of calling the relevant method, but it can also significantly increase code size, which can then negatively impact a whole bunch of things, such as causing the instruction cache to become much less effective. In this case, however, it not only improves throughput but also actually reduces code size. Inlining is a powerful optimization, not just because it eliminates the overhead of a call, but because it exposes the contents of the callee to the caller. The JIT generally doesn’t do interprocedural analysis, due to the JIT’s limited time budget for optimizations, but inlining overcomes that by merging the caller and the callee, at which point the JIT optimizations of the caller factor in the callee. Imagine a method public static int GetValue() => 42; and a caller that does if (GetValue() * 2 > 100) { ... lots of code ... }. If GetValue() isn’t inlined, that comparison and “lots of code” will get JIT’d, but if GetValue() is inlined, the JIT will see this as if (84 > 100) { ... lots of code ... }, and the whole block will be dropped. Thankfully such a simple method will almost always be automatically inlined, but ImmutableArray<T>‘s GetEnumerator is just large enough that the JIT doesn’t recognize automatically how beneficial it will be. In practice, when the GetEnumerator is inlined, the JIT ends up being able to better recognize that the foreach is iterating over an array, and instead of the generated code for Sum being:

    ImmutableList<T>.Contains also saw significant improvements due to dotnet/corefx#40540 from @shortspider. Contains had been implemented using ImmutableList<T>‘s IndexOf method, which is in turn implemented on top of its Enumerator. Under the covers ImmutableList<T> is implemented today as an AVL tree, a form of self-balancing binary search tree, and in order to walk such a tree in order, it needs to retain a non-trivial amount of state, and ImmutableList<T>‘s enumerator goes to great pains to avoid allocating per enumeration in order to store that state. That results in non-trivial overhead. However, Contains doesn’t care about the exact index of an element in the list (nor which of potentially multiple copies is found), just that it’s there, and as such, it can employ a trivial recursive tree search. (And because the tree is balanced, we’re not concerned about stack overflow conditions.)
    ImmutableList<T>.Contains 也看到了显著的改进，因为来自@shortspider的dotnet/corefx#40540。 Contains 是使用 ImmutableList<T> 的 IndexOf 方法实现的，而该方法又在 Enumerator 之上实现。今天， ImmutableList<T> 被实现为AVL树，一种自平衡二叉搜索树的形式，并且为了按顺序遍历这样的树，它需要保留非平凡数量的状态，并且 ImmutableList<T> 的枚举器非常努力地避免为存储该状态分配每个枚举。这会导致不平凡的开销。然而， Contains 并不关心列表中某个元素的确切索引（也不关心潜在的多个副本中的哪一个），只关心它在那里，因此，它可以使用简单的递归树搜索。(And因为树是平衡的，所以我们不关心堆栈溢出条件。

    LINQ

    Previous releases of .NET Core saw a large amount of churn in the System.Linq codebase, in particular to improve performance. That flow has slowed, but .NET 5 still sees performance improvements in LINQ.
    以前的.NET Core版本在 System.Linq 代码库中出现了大量的流失，特别是为了提高性能。这个流程已经放缓，但.NET 5仍然可以看到LINQ的性能改进。

    One noteable improvement is in OrderBy. As discussed earlier, there were multiple motivations for moving coreclr’s native sorting implementation up into managed code, one of which was being able to reuse it easily as part of span-based sorting methods.     值得注意的是 OrderBy 。如前所述，将coreclr的原生排序实现迁移到托管代码中有多种动机，其中之一是能够将其作为基于span的排序方法的一部分轻松重用。这样的API公开了，通过dotnet/runtime#1888，我们能够在 System.Linq 中利用基于跨度的排序。这尤其是有益的，因为它使得能够利用基于 Comparison<T> 的排序例程，这进而使得能够避免在每个比较操作上的多级间接。

    As a final example, dotnet/corefx#40377 was arguably a long time coming. This is an interesting case to me. For a while now I’ve seen developers assume that Enumerable.Any() is more efficient than Enumerable.Count() != 0; after all, Any() only needs to determine whether there’s anything in the source, and Count() needs to determine how many things there are in the source. Thus, with any reasonable collection, Any() should at worst case be O(1) and Count() may at worst case be O(N), so wouldn’t Any() always be preferable? There are even Roslyn analyzers that recommend this conversion. Unfortunately, it’s not always the case. Until .NET 5, Any() was implemented essentially as follows:
    作为最后一个例子，dotnet/corefx#40377可以说是一个很长的时间到来。这对我来说是个有趣的案例。有一段时间以来，我看到开发人员认为 Enumerable.Any() 比 Enumerable.Count() != 0 更有效率;毕竟 Any() 只需要判断源中有没有东西， Count() 需要判断源中有多少东西。因此，对于任何合理的集合， Any() 在最坏的情况下应该是O（1）， Count() 在最坏的情况下可能是O（N），所以 Any() 不总是更好的吗？甚至有Roslyn分析仪推荐这种转换。不幸的是，情况并非总是如此。在.NET 5之前， Any() 的实现基本如下：

    using (IEnumerator<T> e = source.GetEnumerator)
    return e.MoveNext();

    That means that in the common case, even though it’s likely an O(1) operation, it’s going to result in an enumerator object being allocated as well as two interface dispatches. In contrast, since the initial release of LINQ in .NET Framework 3.0, Count() has had optimized code paths that special-case ICollection<T> to use its Count property, in which case generally it’s going to be O(1) and allocation-free with only one interface dispatch. As a result, for very common cases (like the source being a List<T>), it was actually more efficient to use Count() != 0 than it was to use Any(). While adding an interface check has some overhead, it was worthwhile adding it to make the Any() implementation predictable and consistent with Count(), such that they could be more easily reasoned about and such that the prevailing wisdom about their costs would become correct.
    这意味着在常见的情况下，即使它可能是一个O（1）操作，它将导致分配一个枚举器对象以及两个接口分派。相比之下，自.NET Framework 3.0中的LINQ初始发布以来， Count() 已经优化了代码路径，特殊情况 ICollection<T> 使用其 Count 属性，在这种情况下，通常它将是O（1）和分配自由，只有一个接口分派。因此，对于非常常见的情况（例如源是 List<T> ），使用 Count() != 0 实际上比使用 Any() 更有效。虽然添加接口检查会带来一些开销，但添加它是值得的，以使 Any() 实现与 Count() 一致，这样它们就可以更容易地进行推理，这样关于它们的成本的普遍看法就变得正确了。

    Networking 联网

    Networking is a critical component of almost any application these days, and great networking performance is of paramount important. As such, every release of .NET now sees a lot of attention paid to improving networking performance, and .NET 5 is no exception.
    如今，网络几乎是任何应用程序的关键组成部分，出色的网络性能至关重要。因此，.NET的每个版本现在都关注提高网络性能，.NET 5也不例外。

    Let’s start by looking at some primitives and working our way up. System.Uri is used by most any app to represent urls, and it’s important that it be fast.     After construction, it’s very common for applications to access the various components of a Uri, and that has been improved as well.     Beyond that, there are a myriad of ways code interacts with Uris, many of which have been improved. For example, dotnet/corefx#41772 improved Uri.EscapeDataString and Uri.EscapeUriString, which escape a string according to RFC 3986 and RFC 3987. Both of these methods relied on a shared helper that employed unsafe code, that roundtripped through a char[], and that had a lot of complexity around Unicode handling. This PR rewrote that helper to utilize newer features of .NET, like spans and runes, in order to make the escape operation both safe and fast. For some inputs, the gains are modest, but for inputs involving Unicode or even for long ASCII inputs, the gains are significant.
    除此之外，代码与 Uri 交互的方式有无数种，其中许多都得到了改进。例如，dotnet/corefx#41772改进了 Uri.EscapeDataString 和 Uri.EscapeUriString ，它们根据RFC 3986和RFC 3987转义字符串。这两种方法都依赖于一个共享的助手，该助手使用 unsafe 代码，通过 char[] 进行往返，并且在Unicode处理方面有很多复杂性。这个PR重写了帮助器，以利用.NET的新特性，如span和runes，以使escape操作既安全又快速。对于某些输入，增益是适度的，但对于涉及Unicode的输入，甚至对于长ASCII输入，增益是显著的。

    Moving up the stack, let’s look at System.Net.Sockets. Since the inception of .NET Core, the TechEmpower benchmarks have been used as one way of gauging progress. Previously we focused primarily on the “Plaintext” benchmark, which has a particular set of very low-level performance characteristics, but for this release, we wanted to focus on improving two other benchmarks, “JSON Serialization” and “Fortunes” (the latter involves database access, and despite its name, the costs of the former are primarily about networking speed due to a very small JSON payload involved). Our efforts here were primarily on Linux. And when I say “our”, I’m not just referring to folks that work on the .NET team itself; we had a very productive collaborative effort via a working group that spanned folks beyond the core team, such as with great ideas and contributions from @tmds from Red Hat and @benaadams from Illyriad Games.
    向上移动堆栈，让我们看看 System.Net.Sockets 。自.NET Core诞生以来，TechEmpower基准测试一直被用作衡量进度的一种方法。之前我们主要关注“明文”基准测试，它具有一组特定的非常低级别的性能特征，但对于这个版本，我们希望专注于改进另外两个基准测试，“JSON序列化”和“Fortunes”（后者涉及数据库访问，尽管名称不同，前者的成本主要是网络速度，因为涉及的JSON负载非常小）。我们的工作主要是在Linux上。当我说“我们的”时，我不仅仅指的是在.NET团队中工作的人;我们通过一个工作组进行了非常富有成效的合作，该工作组跨越了核心团队之外的人员，例如Red Hat的@tmds和Illyriad Games的@benaadams的伟大想法和贡献。

    On Linux, the Sockets implementation is based on epoll. To achieve the huge scale demanded of many services, we can’t just dedicate a thread per Socket, which is where we’d be if blocking I/O were employed for all operations on the Socket. Instead, non-blocking I/O is used, and when the operating system isn’t ready to fulfill a request (e.g. when ReadAsync is used on a Socket but there’s no data available to read, or when SendAsync is used on a Socket but there’s no space available in the kernel’s send buffer), epoll is used to notify the Socket implementation of a change in the socket’s status so that the operation can be tried again. epoll is a way of using one thread to block efficiently waiting for changes on any number of sockets, and so the implementation maintains a dedicated thread for waiting for changes on all of the Sockets registered with that epoll. The implementation maintained multiple epoll threads, generally a number equal to half the number of cores in the system. With multiple Sockets all multiplexed onto the same epoll and epoll thread, the implementation needs to be very careful not to run arbitrary work in response to a socket notification; doing so would happen on the epoll thread itself, and thus the epoll thread wouldn’t be able to process further notifications until that work completed. Worse, if that work blocked waiting for another notification on any of the Sockets associated with that same epoll, the system would deadlock. As such, the thread processing the epoll tried to do as little work as possible in response to a socket notification, extracting just enough information to queue the actual processing to the thread pool.
    在Linux上， Sockets 实现基于epoll。为了实现许多服务所需的巨大规模，我们不能仅仅为每个 Socket 专用一个线程，如果Socket上的所有操作都采用阻塞I/O，我们就会这样做。相反，使用非阻塞I/O，并且当操作系统未准备好满足请求时（例如，当 ReadAsync 在 Socket 上使用但没有数据可供读取时，或者当 SendAsync 在 Socket 上使用但内核的发送缓冲区中没有可用空间时，epoll用于通知 Socket 实现套接字状态的改变，以便可以再次尝试该操作。epoll是一种使用一个线程来有效地阻止等待任何数目的套接字上的变化的方式，因此该实现维护了一个专用线程来等待向该epoll注册的所有 Socket 的变化。该实现维护了多个epoll线程，其数量通常等于系统中核数的一半。 由于多个 Socket 都复用到同一个epoll和epoll线程上，实现需要非常小心，不要在响应套接字通知时运行任意工作;这样做将发生在epoll线程本身上，因此epoll线程将无法处理进一步的通知，直到该工作完成。更糟糕的是，如果该工作阻塞等待与同一epoll相关的任何 Socket 的另一个通知，系统将死锁。因此，处理epoll的线程尝试做尽可能少的工作来响应套接字通知，提取刚好足够的信息来将实际处理排队到线程池。

    It turns out that there was an interesting feedback loop happening between these epoll threads and the thread pool. There was just enough overhead in queueing the work items from the epoll threads that multiple epoll threads were warranted, but multiple epoll threads resulted in some contention on that queueing, such that every additional thread added more than its fair share of overhead. On top of that, the rate of queueing was just low enough that the thread pool would have trouble keeping all of its threads saturated in the case where a very small amount of work would happen in response to a socket operation (which is the case with the JSON serialization benchmark); this would in turn result in the thread pool spending more time sequestering and releasing threads, which made it slower, which created a feedback loop. Long story short, less-than-ideal queueing led to slower processing and more epoll threads than truly needed. This was rectified with two PRs, dotnet/runtime#35330 and dotnet/runtime#35800. #35330 changed the queueing model from the epoll threads such that rather than queueing one work item per event (when the epoll wakes up in response to a notification, there may actually be multiple notifications across all of the sockets registered with it, and it will provide all of those notifications in a batch), it would queue one work item for the whole batch. The pool thread processing it then employs a model very much like how Parallel.For/ForEach have worked for years, which is that the queued work item can reserve a single item for itself and then queue a replica of itself to help process the remainder. This changes the calculus such that, on most reasonable sized machines, it actually becomes beneficial to have fewer epoll threads rather than more (and, not coincidentally, we want there to be fewer), so #35800 then changes the number of epoll threads used such that there typically ends up just being one (on machines with much larger core counts, there may still be more). We also made the epoll count configurable via the DOTNET_SYSTEM_NET_SOCKETS_THREAD_COUNT environment variable, which can be set to the desired count in order to override the system’s defaults if a developer wants to experiment with other counts and provide feedback on their results for their given workload.
    事实证明，在这些epoll线程和线程池之间发生了一个有趣的反馈循环。将来自epoll线程的工作项排队的开销刚好足够多，多个epoll线程是可以保证的，但是多个epoll线程导致了排队的一些争用，使得每个额外的线程增加的开销超过了其公平份额。最重要的是，队列的速率非常低，以至于线程池在响应套接字操作时只发生少量工作（JSON序列化基准测试就是这种情况）的情况下很难保持其所有线程饱和;这又将导致线程池花费更多的时间隔离和释放线程，这使得线程池更慢，这产生了反馈循环。长话短说，不太理想的排队导致了处理速度较慢，并导致了比实际需要更多的epoll线程。 使用两个PR，dotnet/runtime#35330和dotnet/runtime#35800纠正了这一点。#35330改变了epoll线程的排队模型，使得不是每个事件排队一个工作项（当epoll响应于通知而唤醒时，实际上可能存在跨向其注册的所有套接字的多个通知，并且它将在一批中提供所有这些通知），而是将为整个批对一个工作项进行排队。池线程处理它然后采用一个非常类似于 Parallel.For/ForEach 多年来工作的模型，即排队的工作项目可以为自己保留单个项目，然后排队自己的副本以帮助处理剩余的项目。 这改变了演算，使得在大多数大小合理的机器上，使用更少的epoll线程实际上变得有益（而且，并非巧合的是，我们希望有更少的线程），所以#35800然后改变了使用的epoll线程的数量，使得通常只有一个（在具有更大内核数量的机器上，可能仍然有更多）。我们还通过 DOTNET_SYSTEM_NET_SOCKETS_THREAD_COUNT 环境变量使epoll计数可配置，该变量可以设置为所需的计数，以便在开发人员想要试验其他计数并提供关于给定工作负载结果的反馈时覆盖系统的默认值。

    As an experiment, in dotnet/runtime#37974 from @tmds we’ve also added an experimental mode (triggered by setting the DOTNET_SYSTEM_NET_SOCKETS_INLINE_COMPLETIONS environment variable to 1 on Linux) where we avoid queueing work to the thread pool at all, and instead just run all socket continuations (e.g. the Work() in await socket.ReadAsync(); Work();); on the epoll threads. Hic sunt dracones! If a socket continuation stalls, no other work associated with that epoll thread will be processed. Worse, if that continuation actually synchronously blocks waiting for other work associated with that epoll, the system will deadlock. However, it’s possible a well-crafted program could achieve better performance in this mode, as the locality of processing could be better and the overhead of queueing to the thread pool could be avoided. Since all sockets work is then run on the epoll threads, it no longer makes sense to default to one; instead it defaults to a number of threads equal to the number of processors. Again, this is an experiment, and we’d welcome feedback on any positive or negative results you see.
    作为一个实验，在@tmds的dotnet/runtime#37974中，我们还添加了一个实验模式（在Linux上，通过将 DOTNET_SYSTEM_NET_SOCKETS_INLINE_COMPLETIONS 环境变量设置为 1 触发），我们完全避免将工作排队到线程池，而是只运行所有套接字延续（例如： Work() 在 await socket.ReadAsync(); Work(); 中）;关于Epoll Threads嘿！如果套接字延续暂停，则不会处理与该epoll线程相关联的其他工作。更糟糕的是，如果该延续实际上同步阻止了等待与该epoll相关的其他工作，则系统将死锁。然而，一个精心设计的程序可能在这种模式下获得更好的性能，因为处理的局部性可以更好，并且可以避免排队到线程池的开销。由于所有套接字的工作都是在epoll线程上运行的，所以默认为一个不再有意义;相反，它默认为等于处理器数量的线程数量。 再说一次，这是一个实验，我们欢迎你看到的任何积极或消极的结果反馈。

    There were some other impactful changes as well. In dotnet/runtime#36371, @tmds changed some of the syscalls used for send and receive operations. In the name of simplicity, the original implementation used the sendmsg and recvmsg syscalls for sending and receiving on sockets, regardless of how many buffers of data were being provided (these operations support vectored I/O, where multiple buffers rather than just one can be passed to each method). It turns out that there’s measurable overhead in doing so when there’s just one buffer, and #36371 was able to reduce the overhead of typical SendAsync and ReceiveAsync operations by preferring to use the send and recv syscalls when appropriate. In dotnet/runtime#36705 @tmds also changed how requests for socket operations are handled to use a lock-free rather than lock-based approach, in order to reduce some overheads. And in dotnet/runtime#36997, @benaadams removed some interface casts that were showing up as measureable overhead in the sockets implementation.
    还有其他一些影响深远的变化。在dotnet/runtime#36371中，@tmds更改了一些用于发送和接收操作的syscall。为了简单起见，最初的实现使用 sendmsg 和 recvmsg syscall在套接字上发送和接收，而不管提供了多少数据缓冲区（这些操作支持向量化I/O，其中多个缓冲区而不是一个缓冲区可以被传递给每个方法）。事实证明，当只有一个缓冲区时，这样做会有可测量的开销，并且#36371能够通过在适当的时候更喜欢使用 send 和 recv 系统来减少典型的 SendAsync 和 ReceiveAsync 操作的开销。在dotnet/runtime#36705中，@tmds还改变了套接字操作请求的处理方式，使用无锁而不是基于锁的方法，以减少一些开销。在dotnet/runtime#36997中，@benaadams删除了一些接口转换，这些转换在套接字实现中显示为可测量的开销。

    These improvements are all focused on sockets performance on Linux at scale, making them difficult to demonstrate in a microbenchmark on a single machine. There are other improvements, however, that are easier to see. dotnet/runtime#32271 removed several allocations from Socket.Connect, Socket.Bind, and a few other operations, where unnecessary copies were being made of some state in support of old Code Access Security (CAS) checks that are no longer relevant: the CAS checks were removed long ago, but the clones remained, so this just cleans those up, too. dotnet/runtime#32275 also removed an allocation from the Windows implementation of SafeSocketHandle. dotnet/runtime#787 refactored Socket.ConnectAsync so that it could share the same internal SocketAsyncEventArgs instance that ends up being used subsequently to perform ReceiveAsync operations, thereby avoiding extra allocations for the connect. dotnet/runtime#34175 utilizes the new Pinned Object Heap introduced in .NET 5 to use pre-pinned buffers in various portions of the SocketAsyncEventArgs implementation on Windows instead of having to use a GCHandle to pin (the corresponding functionality on Linux doesn’t require pinning, so it’s not used there). And in dotnet/runtime#37583, @tmds reduced allocations as part of the vectored I/O SendAsync/ReceivedAsync implementations on Unix by employing stack allocation where appropriate.
    这些改进都集中在Linux上的大规模套接字性能上，使得它们很难在单个机器上的微基准测试中演示。然而，还有其他更容易看到的改进。dotnet/runtime#32271删除了 Socket.Connect 、 Socket.Bind 和一些其他操作中的几个分配，其中一些状态的不必要副本被制作以支持旧的代码访问安全（CAS）检查，这些检查不再相关：CAS检查很久以前就被删除了，但克隆仍然存在，所以这只是清理了那些，太。dotnet/runtime#32275还从 SafeSocketHandle 的Windows实现中删除了一个分配。dotnet/runtime#787重构了 Socket.ConnectAsync ，这样它就可以共享同一个内部 SocketAsyncEventArgs 实例，该实例最终被用于执行 ReceiveAsync 操作，从而避免了额外的连接分配。dotnet/runtime#34175利用中引入的新的固定对象堆。NET 5在Windows上的 SocketAsyncEventArgs 实现的各个部分中使用预固定缓冲区，而不是必须使用 GCHandle 来固定（Linux上的相应功能不需要固定，所以它不在那里使用）。在dotnet/runtime#37583中，@tmds通过在适当的情况下使用堆栈分配来减少分配，作为Unix上向量化I/O SendAsync / ReceivedAsync 实现的一部分。

    private Socket _listener, _client, _server;
private byte[] _buffer = new byte[8];
private List<ArraySegment<byte>> _buffers = new List<ArraySegment<byte>>();

[GlobalSetup]
public void Setup()
{
    _listener = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.Tcp);
    _listener.Bind(new IPEndPoint(IPAddress.Loopback, 0));
    _listener.Listen(1);

    _client = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.Tcp);
    _client.Connect(_listener.LocalEndPoint);

    _server = _listener.Accept();

    for (int i = 0; i < _buffer.Length; i++)
        _buffers.Add(new ArraySegment<byte>(_buffer, i, 1));
}

[Benchmark]
public async Task SendReceive()
{
    await _client.SendAsync(_buffers, SocketFlags.None);
    int total = 0;
    while (total < _buffer.Length)
        total += await _server.ReceiveAsync(_buffers, SocketFlags.None);
}
    Method 方法 Runtime 运行时 Mean 意味 Ratio 比 Allocated 分配
    SendReceive 发送接收 .NET Core 3.1 5.924 us 5.924美元 1.00 624 B 小行星624 B
    SendReceive 发送接收 .NET 5.0 5.230 us 5.230美元 0.88 144 B 144个B

    On top of that, we come to System.Net.Http. A bunch of improvements were made to SocketsHttpHandler, in two areas in particular. The first is the processing of headers, which represents a significant portion of allocations and processing associated with the type. dotnet/corefx#41640 kicked things off by making the HttpHeaders.TryAddWithoutValidation true to its name: due to how SocketsHttpHandler was enumerating request headers to write them to the wire, it ended up performing the validation on the headers even though the developer specified “WithoutValidation”, and the PR fixed that. Multiple PRs, including dotnet/runtime#35003, dotnet/runtime#34922, dotnet/runtime#32989, and dotnet/runtime#34974 improved lookups in SocketHttpHandler‘s list of known headers (which helps avoid allocations when such headers are present) and augmented that list to be more comprehensive. dotnet/runtime#34902 updated the internal collection type used in various strongly-typed header collections to incur less allocation, and dotnet/runtime#34724 made some of the allocations associated with headers pay-for-play only when they’re actually accessed (and also special-cased Date and Server response headers to avoid allocations for them in the most common cases). The net result is a small improvement to throughput but a significant improvement to allocation:
    在此基础上，我们来到 System.Net.Http 。对 SocketsHttpHandler 进行了一系列改进，特别是在两个方面。第一个是头的处理，它代表了与类型相关联的分配和处理的重要部分。dotnet/corefx#41640通过使 HttpHeaders.TryAddWithoutValidation 与它的名字相符而开始了事情：由于 SocketsHttpHandler 是如何枚举请求头以将它们写入连接的，它最终还是对头执行验证，即使开发人员指定了“WithoutValidation”，PR也修复了这一点。包括dotnet/runtime#35003、dotnet/runtime#34922、dotnet/runtime#32989和dotnet/runtime#34974在内的多个PR改进了在 SocketHttpHandler 的已知报头列表中的查找（这有助于避免当存在这样的报头时分配），并扩充了该列表以更全面。 dotnet/runtime#34902更新了在各种强类型头集合中使用的内部集合类型，以减少分配，dotnet/runtime#34724使一些与头关联的分配仅在它们实际被访问时付费（以及特殊情况的Date和Server响应头，以避免在最常见的情况下为它们分配）。 最终结果是吞吐量有了小幅改善，但分配有了显著改善：

    private static readonly Socket s_listener = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.Tcp);
private static readonly HttpClient s_client = new HttpClient();

[GlobalSetup]
public void CreateSocketServer()
{
    s_listener.Bind(new IPEndPoint(IPAddress.Loopback, 0));
    s_listener.Listen(int.MaxValue);
    var ep = (IPEndPoint)s_listener.LocalEndPoint;
    s_uri = new Uri($"http://{ep.Address}:{ep.Port}/");
    byte[] response = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes("HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nDate: Sun, 05 Jul 2020 12:00:00 GMT \r\nServer: Example\r\nContent-Length: 5\r\n\r\nHello");
    byte[] endSequence = new byte[] { (byte)'\r', (byte)'\n', (byte)'\r', (byte)'\n' };

    Task.Run(async () =>
    {
        while (true)
        {
            Socket s = await s_listener.AcceptAsync();
            _ = Task.Run(() =>
            {
                using (var ns = new NetworkStream(s, true))
                {
                    byte[] buffer = new byte[1024];
                    int totalRead = 0;
                    while (true)
                    {
                        int read =  ns.Read(buffer, totalRead, buffer.Length - totalRead);
                        if (read == 0) return;
                        totalRead += read;
                        if (buffer.AsSpan(0, totalRead).IndexOf(endSequence) == -1)
                        {
                            if (totalRead == buffer.Length) Array.Resize(ref buffer, buffer.Length * 2);
                            continue;
                        }

                        ns.Write(response, 0, response.Length);

                        totalRead = 0;
                    }
                }
            });
        }
    });
}

    Some other header-related PRs were more specialized. For example, dotnet/runtime#34860 improved parsing of the Date header just by being more thoughtful about the approach. The previous implementation was using DateTime.TryParseExact with a long list of viable formats; that knocks the implementation off its fast path and causes it to be much slower to parse even when the input matches the first format in the list. And in the case of Date headers today, the vast majority of headers will follow the format outlined in RFC 1123, aka “r”. Thanks to improvements in previous releases, DateTime‘s parsing of the “r” format is very fast, so we can just try that one directly first with the TryParseExact for a single format, and only if it fails fall back to the TryParseExact with the remainder.
    其他一些与主管相关的PR更加专业化。例如，dotnet/runtime#34860改进了Date头的解析，只是通过对该方法进行了更深入的思考。以前的实现是使用 DateTime.TryParseExact 和一长串可行格式;这会使实现偏离其快速路径，并导致即使输入与列表中的第一种格式匹配时，解析起来也要慢得多。在今天的Date头的情况下，绝大多数头将遵循RFC 1123中概述的格式，又名“r”。由于之前版本的改进， DateTime 解析“r”格式非常快，所以我们可以直接用 TryParseExact 来尝试一种格式，只有当失败时，我们才用其余的版本返回到 TryParseExact 。

    The biggest improvements, however, came for HTTP/2 in general. In .NET Core 3.1, the HTTP/2 implementation was functional, but not particularly tuned, and so some effort for .NET 5 went into making the HTTP/2 implementation better, and in particular more scalable. dotnet/runtime#32406 and dotnet/runtime#32624 significantly reduced allocations involved in HTTP/2 GET requests by employing a custom CopyToAsync override on the response stream used for HTTP/2 responses, by being more careful around how request headers are accessed as part of writing out the request (in order to avoid forcing lazily-initialized state into existence when it’s not necessary), and removing async-related allocations. And dotnet/runtime#32557 reduced allocations in HTTP/2 POST requests by being better about how cancellation was handled and reducing allocation associated with async operations there, too. On top of those, dotnet/runtime#35694 included a bunch of HTTP/2-related changes, including reducing the number of locks involved (HTTP/2 involves more synchronization in the C# implementation than HTTP/1.1, because in HTTP/2 multiple requests are multiplexed onto the same socket connection), reducing the amount of work done while holding locks, in one key case changing the kind of locking mechanism used, adding more headers to the known headers optimization, and a few other tweaks to reduce overheads. As a follow-up, dotnet/runtime#36246 removed some allocations due to cancellation and trailing headers (which are common in gRPC traffic). To demo this, I created a simple ASP.NET Core localhost server (using the Empty template and removing a small amount of code not needed for this example):
    然而，最大的改进来自HTTP/2。在.NET Core 3.1中，HTTP/2实现是功能性的，但没有特别调优，因此.NET 5的一些努力致力于使HTTP/2实现更好，尤其是更具可伸缩性。dotnet/runtime#32406和dotnet/runtime#32624通过在用于HTTP/2响应的响应流上使用自定义 CopyToAsync 覆盖，通过在写出请求时更加小心地访问请求头，从而显著减少了HTTP/2 GET请求中涉及的分配（为了避免在不必要的情况下强制惰性初始化状态存在），并删除异步相关的分配。dotnet/runtime#32557减少了HTTP/2 POST请求中的分配，因为它更好地处理取消的方式，并减少了与异步操作相关的分配。 最重要的是，dotnet/runtime#35694包括了一系列与HTTP/2相关的更改，包括减少所涉及的锁的数量（HTTP/2在C#实现中比HTTP/1.1涉及更多的同步，因为在HTTP/2中多个请求被复用到同一个套接字连接上），减少持有锁时完成的工作量，在一个关键的例子中改变了所使用的锁机制的种类，在已知的头优化中添加更多的头，以及一些其他的调整来减少开销。作为后续行动，dotnet/runtime#36246删除了一些分配，因为取消和尾随报头（这在gRPC流量中很常见）。为了演示这一点，我创建了一个简单的ASP。NET Core localhost服务器（使用Empty模板并删除了本示例不需要的少量代码）：

    Trimming 修剪

    Up until .NET Core 3.0, .NET Core was focused primarily on server workloads, with ASP.NET Core being the preeminent application model on the platform. With .NET Core 3.0, Windows Forms and Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) were added, bringing .NET Core to desktop applications. With .NET Core 3.2, Blazor support for browser applications was released, but based on mono and the library’s from the mono stack. With .NET 5, Blazor uses the .NET 5 mono runtime and all of the same .NET 5 libraries shared by every other app model. This brings an important twist to performance: size. While code size has always been an important issue (and is important for .NET Native applications), the scale required for a successful browser-based deployment really brings it to the forefront, as we need to be concerned about download size in a way we haven’t focused with .NET Core in the past.
    在.NET Core 3.0之前，.NET Core主要专注于服务器工作负载，ASP.NET Core是平台上最优秀的应用程序模型。在.NET Core 3.0中，添加了Windows Forms和Windows Presentation Foundation（WPF），将.NET Core引入桌面应用程序。随着.NET Core 3.2，Blazor对浏览器应用程序的支持被发布，但基于mono和来自mono堆栈的库。在.NET 5中，Blazor使用.NET 5 mono运行时和所有其他应用模型共享的相同.NET 5库。这给性能带来了一个重要的转折：尺寸虽然代码大小一直是一个重要的问题（对于.NET Native应用程序也很重要），但成功的基于浏览器的部署所需的规模确实使其成为最重要的问题，因为我们需要关注下载大小，而我们过去没有关注.NET Core。

    To assist with application size, the .NET SDK includes a linker that’s capable of trimming away unused portions of the app, not only at the assembly level, but also at the member level, doing static analysis to determine what code is and isn’t used and throwing away the parts that aren’t. This brings an interesting set of challenges: some coding patterns employed for convenience or simplified API consumption are difficult for the linker to analyze in a way that would allow it to throw away much of anything. As a result, one of the big performance-related efforts in .NET 5 is around improving the trimmability of the libraries.
    为了帮助调整应用程序的大小，.NET SDK包含了一个链接器，该链接器能够修剪应用程序的未使用部分，不仅在程序集级别，而且在成员级别，进行静态分析以确定哪些代码被使用和不被使用，并丢弃哪些部分未使用。这带来了一系列有趣的挑战：为了方便或简化API使用而采用的一些编码模式对于链接器来说很难以允许它丢弃任何东西的方式进行分析。因此，.NET 5中与性能相关的一项重要工作就是改进库的可微调性。

    There are two facets to this:
    这有两个方面：

    1. Not removing too much (correctness). We need to make sure that the libraries can actually be trimmed safely. In particular, reflection (even reflection only over public surface area) makes it difficult for the linker to find all members that may actually be used, e.g. code in one place in the app uses typeof to get a Type instance, and passes that to another part of the app that uses GetMethod to retrieve a MethodInfo for a public method on that type, and passes that MethodInfo to another part of the app which invokes it. To address that, the linker employs heuristics to minimize false positives on APIs that can be removed, but to help it further, a bunch of attributes have been added in .NET 5 that enable developers to make such implicit dependencies explicit, to suppress warnings from the linker on things it might deem to be unsafe but actually aren’t, and to force warnings onto consumers to say that certain portions of the surface area simply aren’t amenable to linking. See dotnet/runtime#35387.
      不要删除太多（正确性）。我们需要确保库实际上可以安全地被修剪。特别地，反射（甚至仅在公共表面区域上反射）使得链接器难以找到实际上可能使用的所有成员，例如应用程序中一个地方的代码使用 typeof 获取 Type 实例，并将其传递给应用程序的另一部分，该部分使用 GetMethod 检索该类型上的公共方法的 MethodInfo ，并将 MethodInfo 传递给调用该应用程序的另一部分。为了解决这个问题，链接器使用启发式方法来最大限度地减少可以删除的API上的误报，但为了进一步帮助它，在.NET 5中添加了一堆属性，使开发人员能够将这种隐式依赖显式化，以抑制链接器对它可能认为不安全但实际上并不安全的东西发出警告，并强制向消费者发出警告，说表面区域的某些部分根本不适合链接。参见dotnet/runtime#35387。
    2. Removing as much as possible (performance). We need to minimize the reasons why pieces of code need to be kept around. This can manifest as refactoring implementations to change calling patterns, it can manifest as using conditions the linker can recognize and use to trim out whole swaths of code, and it can manifest as using finer-grained controls over exactly what needs to be kept and why.
      尽可能地删除（性能）。我们需要最小化为什么需要保留代码片段的原因。这可以表现为重构实现以改变调用模式，它可以表现为使用链接器可以识别和使用的条件来修剪整个代码，它可以表现为使用更细粒度的控制来精确地控制需要保留的内容和原因。

    There are many examples of the second, so I’ll highlight a few to showcase the various techniques employed:
    第二种方法有很多例子，所以我将重点介绍几种方法来展示所采用的各种技术：

    • Removing unnecessary code, such as in dotnet/corefx#41177. Here we find a lot of antiquated TraceSource/Switch usage, which only existed to enable some debug-only tracing and asserts, but which no one was actually using anymore, and which were causing some of these types to be seen by the linker as used even in release builds.
      删除不必要的代码，例如dotnet/corefx#41177。在这里我们发现了很多过时的 TraceSource / Switch 用法，它们只是为了启用一些仅调试的跟踪和断言而存在的，但实际上没有人再使用它们了，并且导致链接器看到这些类型中的一些甚至在发布版本中使用。
    • Removing antiquated code that once served a purpose but no longer does, such as in dotnet/coreclr#26750. This type used to be important to help improve ngen (the predecessor of crossgen), but it’s no longer needed. Or such as in dotnet/coreclr#26603, where some code was no longer actually used, but was causing types to be kept around nonetheless.
      删除曾经有过用途但不再有用途的过时代码，例如dotnet/coreclr#26750。这种类型曾经对改进ngen（crossgen的前身）很重要，但现在不再需要了。或者像在dotnet/coreclr#26603中，一些代码实际上不再使用，但仍然导致类型被保留。
    • Removing duplicate code, such as in dotnet/corefx#41165, dotnet/corefx#40935, and dotnet/coreclr#26589. Several libraries were using their own private copy of some hash code helper routines, resulting in each having its own copy of IL for that functionality. They could instead be updated to use the shared HashCode type, which not only helps in IL size and trimming, but also helps to avoid extra code that needs to be maintained and to better modernize the codebase to utilize the functionality we’re recommending others use as well.
      删除重复代码，例如dotnet/corefx#41165、dotnet/corefx#40935和dotnet/coreclr#26589中的重复代码。有几个库使用了自己的一些散列代码助手例程的私有副本，导致每个库都有自己的IL副本用于该功能。它们可以被更新为使用共享的 HashCode 类型，这不仅有助于IL大小和修剪，而且有助于避免需要维护的额外代码，并更好地更新代码库，以利用我们推荐的其他人使用的功能。
    • Using different APIs, such as in dotnet/corefx#41143. Code was using extension helper methods that were resulting in additional types being pulled in, but the “help” provided actually saved little-to-no code. A potentially better example is dotnet/corefx#41142, which removed use of the non-generic Queue and Stack types from the System.Xml implementations, instead using only the generic implementations (dotnet/coreclr#26597 did something similar, with WeakReference). Or dotnet/corefx#41111, which changed some code in the XML library to use HttpClient rather than WebRequest, which allowed removing the entire System.Net.Requests dependency. Or dotnet/corefx#41110, which avoided System.Net.Http needing to use System.Text.RegularExpressions: it was unnecessary complication that could be replaced with a tiny amount of code specific to that use case. Another example is dotnet/coreclr#26602, where some code was unnecessarily using string.ToLower(), and replacing its usage was not only more efficient, it helped to enable that overload to be trimmed away by default. dotnet/coreclr#26601 is similar.
      使用不同的API，例如dotnet/corefx#41143。代码使用了扩展帮助器方法，这些方法导致了额外的类型被拉入，但是提供的“帮助”实际上节省了很少的代码。一个可能更好的例子是dotnet/corefx#41142，它从 System.Xml 实现中删除了非泛型 Queue 和 Stack 类型的使用，而只使用泛型实现（dotnet/coreclr#26597对 WeakReference 做了类似的事情）。或者dotnet/corefx#41111，它将XML库中的一些代码更改为使用 HttpClient 而不是 WebRequest ，这允许删除整个 System.Net.Requests 依赖项。或者dotnet/corefx#41110，避免了 System.Net.Http 需要使用 System.Text.RegularExpressions ：这是不必要的复杂性，可以用特定于用例的少量代码来代替。另一个例子是dotnet/coreclr#26602，其中一些代码不必要地使用了 string.ToLower() ，替换它的用法不仅更有效，还有助于默认情况下删除重载。 dotnet/coreclr#26601类似。
    • Rerouting logic to avoid rooting large swaths of unneeded code, such as in dotnet/corefx#41075. If code just used new Regex(string), that internally just delegated to the longer Regex(string, RegexOptions) constructor, and that constructor needs to be able to use the internal RegexCompiler in case the RegexOptions.Compiled is used. By tweaking the code paths such that the Regex(string) constructor doesn’t depend on the Regex(string, RegexOptions) constructor, it becomes trivial for the linker to remove the whole RegexCompiler code path (and its dependency on reflection emit) if it’s not otherwise used. dotnet/corefx#41101 then took better advantage of this by ensuring the shorter calls could be used when possible. This is a fairly common pattern for avoiding such unnecessary rooting. Consider Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(string). It used to call to the Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(string, EnvironmentVariableTarget) overload, passing in the default EnvironmentVariableTarget.Process. Instead, the dependency was inverted: the Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(string) overload contains only the logic for handling the Process case, and then the longer overload has if (target == EnvironmentVariableTarget.Process) return GetEnvironmentVariable(name);. That way, the most common case of just using the simple overload doesn’t pull in all of the code paths necessary to handle the other much less common targets. dotnet/corefx#0944 is another example: for apps that just write to the console rather than also read from the console, it enables a lot more of the console internals to be linked away.
      重新路由逻辑，以避免根大量不需要的代码，如dotnet/corefx#41075。如果代码只使用 new Regex(string) ，则内部将其委托给较长的 Regex(string, RegexOptions) 构造函数，并且该构造函数需要能够在使用 RegexOptions.Compiled 的情况下使用内部 RegexCompiler 。通过调整代码路径，使 Regex(string) 构造函数不依赖于 Regex(string, RegexOptions) 构造函数，链接器移除整个 RegexCompiler 代码路径（及其对反射发射的依赖）变得微不足道，如果没有其他方式使用。然后dotnet/corefx#41101通过确保尽可能使用较短的呼叫来更好地利用这一点。这是一个相当常见的模式，以避免这种不必要的生根。考虑 Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(string) 。它曾经调用 Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(string, EnvironmentVariableTarget) 重载，传入默认的 EnvironmentVariableTarget.Process 。相反，依赖关系被颠倒了： Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(string) 重载仅包含用于处理 Process 情况的逻辑，然后较长的重载具有 if (target == EnvironmentVariableTarget.Process) return GetEnvironmentVariable(name); 。 这样，最常见的情况是，仅仅使用简单重载并没有引入处理其他不太常见的目标所必需的所有代码路径。dotnet/corefx#0944是另一个例子：对于只写入控制台而不是从控制台读取的应用程序，它允许更多的控制台内部部分被链接走。
    • Using lazy initialization, especially for static fields, such as in dotnet/runtime#37909. If a type is used and any of its static methods are called, its static constructor will need to be kept, and any fields initialized by the static constructor will also need to be kept. If such fields are instead lazily initialized on first use, the fields will only need to be kept if the code that performs that lazy initialization is reachable.
      使用延迟初始化，尤其是静态字段，例如在dotnet/runtime#37909中。如果使用了一个类型并且调用了它的任何静态方法，则需要保留它的静态构造函数，并且由静态构造函数初始化的任何字段也需要保留。如果这样的字段在第一次使用时被延迟初始化，则只有当执行延迟初始化的代码可访问时才需要保留这些字段。
    • Using feature switches, such as in dotnet/runtime#38129 (further benefited from in dotnet/runtime#38828). In many cases, whole feature sets may not be necessary for an app, such as logging or debugging support, but from the linker’s perspective, it sees the code being used and thus is forced to keep it. However, the linker is capable of being told about replacement values it should use for known properties, e.g. you can tell the linker that when it sees a Boolean-returning SomeClass.SomeProperty, it should replace it with a constant false, which will in turn enable it to trim out any code guarded by that property.
      使用功能开关，例如在dotnet/runtime#38129中（进一步受益于dotnet/runtime#38828）。在许多情况下，整个功能集可能不是应用程序所必需的，例如日志记录或调试支持，但从链接器的角度来看，它会看到正在使用的代码，因此被迫保留它。然而，连接子能够被告知其应当用于已知性质的替换值，例如，你可以告诉链接器，当它看到一个 Boolean -返回 SomeClass.SomeProperty 时，它应该用一个常量false来替换它，这反过来会使它能够修剪掉由该属性保护的任何代码。
    • Ensuring that test-only code is only in tests, as in dotnet/runtime#38729. In this case, some code intended only to be used for testing was getting compiled into the product assembly, and its tendrils were causing System.Linq.Expressions to be brought in as well.
      确保仅测试代码仅在测试中，如dotnet/runtime#38729。在这种情况下，一些只打算用于测试的代码被编译到产品程序集中，并且它的卷须也导致 System.Linq.Expressions 被引入。

    Peanut Butter 花生酱

    In my .NET Core 3.0 performance post, I talked about “peanut butter”, lots of small improvements here and there that individually don’t necessarily make a huge difference, but are addressing costs that are otherwise smeared across the code, and fixing a bunch of these en mass can make a measurable difference. As with previous releases, there are a myriad of these welcome improvements that have gone into .NET 5. Here’s a smattering:
    在我的.NET Core 3.0性能帖子中，我谈到了“花生酱”，这里和那里的许多小改进，单独的不一定会产生巨大的差异，但解决了否则会在代码中涂抹的成本，修复一堆这样的质量可以产生可衡量的差异。与以前的版本一样，.NET 5中有大量的这些受欢迎的改进。这里有一个小故事：

    • Faster assembly loading. For historical reasons, .NET Core had a lot of tiny implementation assemblies, with the split serving little meaningful purpose. Yet every additional assembly that needs to be loaded adds overhead. dotnet/runtime#2189 and dotnet/runtime#31991 merged a bunch of small assemblies together in order to reduce the number that need to be loaded.
      更快的装配加载。由于历史原因，.NET Core有很多微小的实现程序集，拆分几乎没有什么有意义的用途。然而，需要加载的每个附加程序集都会增加开销。dotnet/runtime#2189和dotnet/runtime#31991将一堆小程序集合并在一起，以减少需要加载的数量。
    • Faster math. dotnet/coreclr#27272 improved checks for NaN, making the code for double.IsNan and float.IsNan smaller code and be faster. dotnet/runtime#35456 from @john-h-k is a nice example of using SSE and AMD64 intrinsics to measurably speed up Math.CopySign and MathF.CopySign. And dotnet/runtime#34452 from @Marusyk improved hash code generation for Matrix3x2 and Matrix4x4.
      更快的数学。dotnet/coreclr#27272改进了NaN的检查，使 double.IsNan 和 float.IsNan 的代码更小，速度更快。来自@john-h-k的dotnet/runtime#35456是一个很好的例子，它使用SSE和AMD 64 intrinsic来显著加速 Math.CopySign 和 MathF.CopySign 。@Marusyk的dotnet/runtime#34452改进了 Matrix3x2 和 Matrix4x4 的哈希代码生成。
    • Faster crypto. In place of open-coded equivalents, dotnet/runtime#36881 from @vcsjones used the optimized BinaryPrimitives in various places within System.Security.Cryptography, yielding more maintainable and faster code, and dotnet/corefx#39600 from @VladimirKhvostov optimized the out-of-favor-but-still-in-use CryptoConfig.CreateFromName method to be upwards of 10x faster.
      更快的加密。代替开放编码的等价物，来自@vcsjones的dotnet/runtime#36881在 System.Security.Cryptography 中的不同地方使用了优化的 BinaryPrimitives ，产生了更易维护和更快的代码，来自@VladimirKhvostov的dotnet/corefx#39600优化了不受欢迎但仍在使用的 CryptoConfig.CreateFromName 方法，速度超过了10倍。
    • Faster interop. dotnet/runtime#36257 reduced entrypoint probing (where the runtime tries to find the exact native function to use for a P/Invoke) by avoiding the Windows-specific “ExactSpelling” checks when on Linux and by setting it to true for more methods when on Windows. dotnet/runtime#33020 from @NextTurn used sizeof(T) instead of Marshal.SizeOf(Type)/Marshal.SizeOf<T>() in a bunch of places, as the former has much less overhead than the latter. And dotnet/runtime#33967, dotnet/runtime#35098, and dotnet/runtime#39059 reduced interop and marshaling costs in several libraries by using more blittable types, using spans and ref locals, using sizeof, and so on.
      更快的互操作dotnet/runtime#36257减少了入口点探测（运行时试图找到用于P/Invoke的确切本机函数），在Linux上避免Windows特定的“ExactSpelling”检查，在Windows上为更多方法设置为true。来自@NextTurn的dotnet/runtime#33020在很多地方使用了 sizeof(T) 而不是 Marshal.SizeOf(Type) / Marshal.SizeOf<T>() ，因为前者的开销比后者少得多。dotnet/runtime#33967、dotnet/runtime#35098和dotnet/runtime#39059通过使用更多的blittable类型、使用spans和ref局部变量、使用 sizeof 等等，减少了几个库中的互操作和封送处理开销。
    • Faster reflection emit. Reflection emit enables developers to write out IL at run-time, and if you can emit the same instructions in a way that takes up less space, you can save on the managed allocations needed to store the sequence. A variety of IL opcodes have shorter variants for more common cases, e.g. Ldc_I4 can be used to load any int value as a constant, but Ldc_I4_S is shorter and can be used to load any sbyte, while Ldc_I4_1 is shorter still and is used to load the value 1. Some libraries take advantage of this and have their own mapping table as part of their emit code to employ the shortest relevant opcode; others don’t. dotnet/runtime#35427 just moved such a mapping into the ILGenerator itself, enabling us to delete all of the customized implementations in the libraries in dotnet/runtime, and get the benefits of the mapping in all of those and others automatically.
      更快的反射发射。反射发出使开发人员能够在运行时写出IL，如果您可以以占用较少空间的方式发出相同的指令，则可以保存存储序列所需的托管分配。各种IL操作码具有更短的变体用于更常见的情况，例如， Ldc_I4 可以用来加载任何 int 值作为常量，但是 Ldc_I4_S 更短，可以用来加载任何 sbyte ，而 Ldc_I4_1 更短，用于加载值 1 。一些库利用了这一点，并将自己的映射表作为其发射代码的一部分，以采用最短的相关操作码;其他人则没有。dotnet/runtime#35427只是将这样的映射移到 ILGenerator 本身中，使我们能够删除dotnet/runtime库中的所有自定义实现，并自动获得所有这些和其他映射的好处。
    • Faster I/O. dotnet/runtime#37705 from @bbartels improved BinaryWriter.Write(string), giving it a fast path for various common inputs. And dotnet/runtime#35978 improved how relationships are managed inside System.IO.Packaging by using O(1) instead of O(N) lookups.  
    • Lots of small allocations here and there. For example, dotnet/runtime#35005 removes a MemoryStream allocation in ByteArrayContent, dotnet/runtime#36228 from @Youssef1313 removes a List<T> and underlying T[] allocation in System.Reflection.MetadataLoadContext, dotnet/runtime#32297 removes a char[] allocation in XmlConverter.StripWhitespace, dotnet/runtime#32276 removes a byte[] allocation on startup in EventSource, dotnet/runtime#32298 removes a char[] allocation in HttpUtility, dotnet/runtime#32299 removes potentially several char[]s in ModuleBuilder, dotnet/runtime#32301 removes some char[] allocations from String.Split usage, dotnet/runtime#32422 removes a char[] allocation in AsnFormatter, dotnet/runtime#34551 removes several string allocations in System.IO.FileSystem, dotnet/corefx#41363 removes a char[] allocation in JsonCamelCaseNamingPolicy, dotnet/coreclr#25631 removes string allocations from MethodBase.ToString(), dotnet/corefx#41274 removes some unnecessary strings from CertificatePal.AppendPrivateKeyInfo, dotnet/runtime#1155 from @Wraith2 removes temporary arrays from SqlDecimal via spans, dotnet/coreclr#26584 removed boxing that previously occurred when using methods like GetHashCode on some tuples, dotnet/coreclr#27451 removed several allocations from reflecting over custom attributes, dotnet/coreclr#27013 remove some string allocations from concatenations by replacing some inputs with consts, and dotnet/runtime#34774 removed some temporary char[] allocations from string.Normalize.  

    New Performance-focused APIs
    新的注重性能的API

    This post has highlighted a plethora of existing APIs that simply get better when running on .NET 5. In addition, there are lots of new APIs in .NET 5, some of which are focused on helping developers to write faster code (many more are focused on enabling developers to perform the same operations with less code, or on enabling new functionality that wasn’t easily accomplished previously) . Here are a few highlights, including in some cases where the APIs are already being used internally by the rest of the libraries to lower costs in existing APIs:
    本文重点介绍了大量现有的API，这些API在.NET 5上运行时会变得更好。此外，.NET 5中还有很多新的API，其中一些专注于帮助开发人员编写更快的代码（更多的是专注于让开发人员能够用更少的代码执行相同的操作，或者启用以前不容易完成的新功能）。以下是一些亮点，包括在某些情况下，API已经被其他库内部使用，以降低现有API的成本：

    • Decimal(ReadOnlySpan<int>) / Decimal.TryGetBits / Decimal.GetBits (dotnet/runtime#32155): In previous releases we added lots of span-based methods for efficiently interacting with primitives, and decimal did get span-based TryFormat and {Try}Parse methods, but these new methods in .NET 5 enable efficiently constructing a decimal from a span as well as extracting the bits from a decimal into a span. You can see this support already being used in SQLDecimal, in BigInteger, in System.Linq.Expressions, and in System.Reflection.Metadata.
      Decimal(ReadOnlySpan<int>) / Decimal.TryGetBits / Decimal.GetBits （dotnet/runtime#32155）：在以前的版本中，我们添加了很多基于span的方法来有效地与原语交互，并且 decimal 确实获得了基于span的 TryFormat 和 {Try}Parse 方法，但是.NET 5中的这些新方法能够有效地从span构造 decimal ，并将 decimal 中的位提取到span中。您可以看到该支持已经在 SQLDecimal 、 BigInteger 、 System.Linq.Expressions 和 System.Reflection.Metadata 中使用。
    • MemoryExtensions.Sort (dotnet/coreclr#27700). I talked about this earlier: new Sort<T> and Sort<TKey, TValue> extension methods enable sorting arbitrary spans of data. These new public methods are already being used in Array itself (dotnet/coreclr#27703) as well as in System.Linq (dotnet/runtime#1888).
      MemoryExtensions.Sort （dotnet/coreclr#27700）。我之前讲过这个：新的 Sort<T> 和 Sort<TKey, TValue> 扩展方法支持对任意范围的数据进行排序。这些新的公共方法已经在 Array 本身（dotnet/coreclr#27703）和 System.Linq （dotnet/runtime#1888）中使用。
    • GC.AllocateArray<T> and GC.AllocateUninitializedArray<T> (dotnet/runtime#33526). These new APIs are like using new T[length], except with two specialized behaviors: using the Uninitialized variant lets the GC hand back arrays without forcefully clearing them (unless they contain references, in which case it must clear at least those), and passing true to the bool pinned argument returns arrays from the new Pinned Object Heap (POH), from which arrays are guaranteed to never be moved in memory such that they can be passed to external code without pinning them (i.e. without using fixed or GCHandle). StringBuilder gained support for using the uninitialized feature (dotnet/coreclr#27364) to reduce the cost of expanding its internal storage, as did the new TranscodingStream (dotnet/runtime#35145), and even the new support for importing X509 certificates and collections from Privacy Enhanced Mail Certificate (PEM) files (dotnet/runtime#38280). You can also see the pinning support being put to good use in the Windows implementation of SocketsAsyncEventArgs (dotnet/runtime#34175), where it needs to allocate pinned buffers for operations like ReceiveMessageFrom.
      GC.AllocateArray<T> 和 GC.AllocateUninitializedArray<T> （dotnet/runtime#33526）。这些新API类似于使用 new T[length] ，除了两个特殊的行为：使用 Uninitialized 变体可以让GC返回数组而不强制清除它们（除非它们包含引用，在这种情况下它必须至少清除那些引用），并且将 true 传递给 bool pinned 参数返回来自新的固定对象堆（POH）的数组，从该新的固定对象堆（POH）中的数组保证不会在内存中移动，这样它们就可以传递给外部代码而不固定它们（即不使用 fixed 或 GCHandle ）。 StringBuilder 获得了使用未初始化功能（dotnet/coreclr#27364）的支持，以减少扩展其内部存储的成本，新的 TranscodingStream （dotnet/runtime#35145）也是如此，甚至新的支持从隐私增强邮件证书（PEM）文件导入X509证书和集合（dotnet/runtime#38280）。 您还可以看到在Windows的 SocketsAsyncEventArgs （dotnet/runtime#34175）实现中很好地使用了固定支持，它需要为像 ReceiveMessageFrom 这样的操作分配固定缓冲区。
    • StringSplitOptions.TrimEntries (dotnet/runtime#35740). String.Split overloads accept a StringSplitOptions enum that enables Split to optionally remove empty entries from the resulting array. The new TrimEntries enum value works with or without this option to first trim results. Regardless of whether RemoveEmptyEntries is used, this enables Split to avoid allocating strings for entries that would become empty once trimmed (or for the allocated strings to be smaller), and then in conjunction with RemoveEmptyEntries for the resulting array to be smaller in such cases. Also, it was found to be common for consumers of Split to subsequently call Trim() on each string, so doing the trimming as part of the Split call can eliminate extra string allocations for the caller. This is used in a handful of types and methods in dotnet/runtime, such as by DataTable, HttpListener, and SocketsHttpHandler.
      StringSplitOptions.TrimEntries （dotnet/runtime#35740）。 String.Split 重载接受一个 StringSplitOptions 枚举，使 Split 可以选择性地从结果数组中删除空条目。新的 TrimEntries 枚举值在使用或不使用此选项的情况下都可用于第一次修剪结果。无论是否使用 RemoveEmptyEntries ，这都使得 Split 能够避免为一旦被修剪就会变为空的条目分配字符串（或者分配的字符串更小），然后与 RemoveEmptyEntries 一起在这种情况下为结果数组更小。此外，发现 Split 的消费者随后在每个字符串上调用 Trim() 是很常见的，因此作为 Split 调用的一部分进行修剪可以消除调用者的额外字符串分配。这在dotnet/runtime中的一些类型和方法中使用，例如 DataTable 、 HttpListener 和 SocketsHttpHandler 。
    • BinaryPrimitives.{Try}{Read/Write}{Double/Single}{Big/Little}Endian (dotnet/runtime#6864). You can see these APIs being used, for example, in the new Concise Binary Object Representation (CBOR) support added in .NET 5 (dotnet/runtime#34046).
      BinaryPrimitives.{Try}{Read/Write}{Double/Single}{Big/Little}Endian （dotnet/runtime#6864）。您可以看到这些API正在使用，例如，在.NET 5（dotnet/runtime#34046）中添加的新的简明二进制对象表示（CBOR）支持中。
    • MailAddress.TryCreate (dotnet/runtime#1052 from @MarcoRossignoli) and PhysicalAddress.{Try}Parse (dotnet/runtime#1057). The new Try overloads enable parsing without exceptions, and the span-based overloads enable parsing addresses from within larger contexts without incurring allocations for substrings.
      MailAddress.TryCreate （来自@MarcoRossignoli的dotnet/runtime#1052）和 PhysicalAddress.{Try}Parse （dotnet/runtime#1057）。新的 Try 重载支持无异常的解析，基于跨度的重载支持从更大的上下文中解析地址，而不会导致子字符串的分配。
    • SocketAsyncEventArgs(bool unsafeSuppressExecutionContextFlow) (dotnet/runtime#706 from @MarcoRossignoli). By default, asynchronous operations in .NET flow ExecutionContext, which means call sites implicitly “capture” the current ExecutionContext and “restore” it when executing the continuation code. This is how AsyncLocal<T> values propagate through asynchronous operations. Such flowing is generally cheap, but there is still a small amount of overhead. As socket operations can be performance-critical, this new constructor on SocketAsyncEventArgs constructor can be used when the developer knows that the context won’t be needed in the callbacks raised by the instance. You can see this used, for example, in SocketHttpHandler‘s internal ConnectHelper (dotnet/runtime#1381).
      SocketAsyncEventArgs(bool unsafeSuppressExecutionContextFlow) （dotnet/runtime#706来自@MarcoRossignoli）。默认情况下，.NET中的异步操作流 ExecutionContext ，这意味着调用站点隐式地“捕获”当前的 ExecutionContext 并在执行继续代码时“还原”它。这就是 AsyncLocal<T> 值通过异步操作传播的方式。这种流动通常是便宜的，但仍然存在少量的开销。由于套接字操作可能是性能关键的，当开发人员知道实例引发的回调中不需要上下文时，可以使用 SocketAsyncEventArgs 构造函数上的这个新构造函数。例如，您可以在 SocketHttpHandler 的内部 ConnectHelper （dotnet/runtime#1381）中看到使用了这一点。
    • Unsafe.SkipInit<T> (dotnet/corefx#41995). The C# compiler’s definite assignment rules require that parameters and locals be assigned to in a variety of situations. In very specific cases, that can require an extra assignment that isn’t actually needed, which, when counting every instruction and memory-write in performance-sensitive code, can be undesirable. This method effectively enables code to pretend it wrote to the parameter or local without actually having done so. This is used in various operations on Decimal (dotnet/runtime#272377), in some of the new APIs on IntPtr and UIntPtr (dotnet/runtime#307 from @john-h-k), in Matrix4x4 (dotnet/runtime#36323 from @eanova), in Utf8Parser (dotnet/runtime#33507), and in UTF8Encoding (dotnet/runtime#31904).
      Unsafe.SkipInit<T> （dotnet/corefx#41995）。C#编译器的明确赋值规则要求在各种情况下为参数和局部变量赋值。在非常特定的情况下，这可能需要一个实际上并不需要的额外赋值，当计算性能敏感代码中的每条指令和内存写入时，这可能是不可取的。此方法有效地使代码可以假装它写入参数或局部，而实际上没有这样做。这被用于 Decimal 的各种操作（dotnet/runtime#272377）， IntPtr 和 UIntPtr 的一些新API（来自@john-h-k的dotnet/runtime#307）， Matrix4x4 （来自@eanova的dotnet/runtime#36323）， Utf8Parser （dotnet/runtime#33507）和 UTF8Encoding （dotnet/runtime#31904）。
    • SuppressGCTransitionAttribute (dotnet/coreclr#26458). This is an advanced attribute for use with P/Invokes that enables the runtime to suppress the cooperative-to-preemptive mode transition it would normally incur, as it does when making internal “FCalls” into the runtime itself. This attribute needs to be used with extreme care (see the detailed comments in the attribute’s description). Even so, you can see it’s used by a few methods in Corelib (dotnet/runtime#27473), and there are pending changes for the JIT that will make it even better (dotnet/runtime#39111).
      SuppressGCTransitionAttribute （dotnet/coreclr#26458）。这是一个用于P/Invokes的高级属性，它使运行库能够抑制通常会引发的合作到抢占模式转换，就像在运行库本身中进行内部“FCallows”时所做的那样。使用此属性时需要格外小心（请参阅属性描述中的详细注释）。即便如此，您也可以看到Corelib中的一些方法使用了它（dotnet/runtime#27473），并且JIT有一些待定的更改将使它变得更好（dotnet/runtime#39111）。
    • CollectionsMarshal.AsSpan (dotnet/coreclr#26867). This method gives callers span-based access to the backing store of a List<T>.
      CollectionsMarshal.AsSpan （dotnet/coreclr#26867）。此方法使调用方能够基于跨度访问 List<T> 的后备存储。
    • MemoryMarshal.GetArrayDataReference (dotnet/runtime#1036). This method returns a reference to the first element of an array (or to where it would have been if the array wasn’t empty). No validation is performed, so it’s both dangerous and very fast. This method is used in a bunch of places in Corelib, all for very low-level optimizations. For example, it’s used as part of the previously-discussed cast helpers implemented in C# (dotnet/runtime#1068) and as part of using Buffer.Memmove in various places (dotnet/runtime#35733).
      MemoryMarshal.GetArrayDataReference （dotnet/runtime#1036）。此方法返回对数组第一个元素的引用（或者如果数组不为空，则返回该元素的位置）。不执行验证，所以它既危险又快速。这种方法在Corelib中的很多地方都使用，所有这些都是用于非常低级的优化。例如，它被用作前面讨论的C#中实现的强制转换帮助器的一部分（dotnet/runtime#1068），以及在不同地方使用 Buffer.Memmove 的一部分（dotnet/runtime#35733）。
    • SslStreamCertificateContext (dotnet/runtime#38364]. When SslStream.AuthenticateAsServer{Async} is provided with the certificate to use, it tries to build the complete X509 chain, an operation which can have varying amounts of associated cost and even perform I/O if additional certificate information needs to be downloaded. In some circumstances, that could happen for the same certificate used to create any number of SslStream instances, resulting in duplicated expense. SslStreamCertificateContext serves as a sort of cache for the results of such a computation, with the work able to be performed once in advanced and then passed to SslStream for any amount of reuse. This helps to avoid that duplicated effort, while also giving callers more predictability and control over any failures.
      SslStreamCertificateContext （dotnet/runtime#38364）。当 SslStream.AuthenticateAsServer{Async} 提供了要使用的证书时，它会尝试构建完整的X509链，这一操作可能会有不同的相关成本，如果需要下载额外的证书信息，甚至会执行I/O。在某些情况下，用于创建任意数量的 SslStream 实例的同一证书可能会发生这种情况，从而导致重复支出。 SslStreamCertificateContext 作为这样的计算结果的一种缓存，工作能够提前执行一次，然后传递给 SslStream 以进行任何数量的重用。这有助于避免重复工作，同时也为呼叫者提供了更多的可预测性和对任何故障的控制。
    • HttpClient.Send (dotnet/runtime#34948). It may be strange to some readers to see a synchronous API called out here. While HttpClient was designed for asynchronous usage, we have found situations where developers are unable to utilize asynchrony, such as when implementing an interface method that’s only synchronous, or being called from a native operation that requires a response synchronously, yet the need to download data is ubiquitous. In these cases, forcing the developer to perform “sync over async” (meaning performing an asynchronous operation and then blocking waiting for it to complete) performs and scales worse than if a synchronous operation were used in the first place. As such, .NET 5 sees limited new synchronous surface area added to HttpClient and its supporting types. dotnet/runtime does itself have use for this in a few places. For example, on Linux when the X509Certificates support needs to download a certificate as part of chain building, it is generally on a code path that needs to be synchronous all the way back to an OpenSSL callback; previously this would use HttpClient.GetByteArrayAsync and then block waiting for it to complete, but that was shown to cause noticeable scalability problems for some users… dotnet/runtime#38502 changed it to use the new sync API instead. Similarly, the older HttpWebRequest type is built on top of HttpClient, and in previous releases of .NET Core, its synchronous GetResponse() method was actually doing sync-over-async; as of dotnet/runtime#39511, it’s now using the synchronous HttpClient.Send method.
      HttpClient.Send （dotnet/runtime#34948）。对于一些读者来说，看到这里调用了一个同步API可能会感到奇怪。虽然 HttpClient 是为异步使用而设计的，但我们发现开发人员无法使用异步的情况，例如当实现一个仅是同步的接口方法时，或者从一个需要同步响应的本地操作调用时，但下载数据的需求无处不在。在这些情况下，强迫开发人员执行“异步同步”（意味着执行异步操作，然后阻塞等待它完成）的执行和扩展比如果首先使用同步操作更差。因此，.NET 5看到了添加到 HttpClient 及其支持类型的有限的新同步表面区域。dotnet/runtime本身确实在一些地方使用这一点。 例如，在Linux上，当 X509Certificates 支持需要下载证书作为链构建的一部分时，它通常是在代码路径上，需要一直同步到OpenSSL回调;以前，这将使用 HttpClient.GetByteArrayAsync ，然后阻止等待它完成，但这被证明会导致一些用户明显的可伸缩性问题...... dotnet/runtime#38502将其改为使用新的sync API。类似地，旧的 HttpWebRequest 类型是在 HttpClient 之上构建的，在以前的.NET Core版本中，它的同步 GetResponse() 方法实际上是同步over-async;从dotnet/runtime#39511开始，它现在使用synchronous HttpClient.Send 方法。
    • HttpContent.ReadAsStream (dotnet/runtime#37494). This is logically part of the HttpClient.Send effort mentioned above, but I’m calling it out separately because it’s useful on its own. The existing ReadAsStreamAsync method is a bit of an oddity. It was originally exposed as async just in case a custom HttpContent-derived type would require that, but it’s extremely rare to find any overrides of HttpContent.ReadAsStreamAsync that aren’t synchronous, and the implementation returned from requests made on HttpClient are all synchronous. As a result, callers end up paying for the Task<Stream> wrapper object for the returned Stream, when in practice it’s always immediately available. Thus, the new ReadAsStream method can actually be useful in such cases to avoid the extra Task<Stream> allocation. You can see it being employed in that manner in dotnet/runtime in various places, such as by the ClientWebSocket implementation.
      HttpContent.ReadAsStream （dotnet/runtime#37494）。从逻辑上讲，这是上面提到的 HttpClient.Send 努力的一部分，但我将其单独调用，因为它本身是有用的。现有的 ReadAsStreamAsync 方法有点奇怪。它最初是以async形式公开的，以防自定义HttpContent派生类型需要，但很少找到任何不同步的 HttpContent.ReadAsStreamAsync 覆盖，并且从 HttpClient 上发出的请求返回的实现都是同步的。结果，调用者最终要为返回的 Stream 支付 Task<Stream> 包装器对象的费用，而实际上它总是立即可用。因此，新的 ReadAsStream 方法在这种情况下实际上可以是有用的，以避免额外的 Task<Stream> 分配。您可以看到它在dotnet/runtime中的各种地方被以这种方式使用，例如 ClientWebSocket 实现。
    • Non-generic TaskCompletionSource (dotnet/runtime#37452). Since Task and Task<T> were introduced, TaskCompletionSource<T> was a way of constructing tasks that would be completed manually by the caller via it’s {Try}Set methods. And since Task<T> derives from Task, the single generic type could be used for both generic Task<T> and non-generic Task needs. However, this wasn’t always obvious to folks, leading to confusion about the right solution for the non-generic case, compounded by the ambiguity about which type to use for T when it was just throw-away. .NET 5 adds a non-generic TaskCompletionSource, which not only eliminates the confusion, but helps a bit with performance as well, as it avoids the task needing to carry around space for a useless T.
      非通用 TaskCompletionSource （dotnet/runtime#37452）。由于 Task 和 Task<T> 被引入， TaskCompletionSource<T> 是一种构造任务的方式，这些任务将由调用者通过它的 {Try}Set 方法手动完成。由于 Task<T> 源自 Task ，单个泛型类型可以用于泛型 Task<T> 和非泛型 Task 的需求。然而，这对人们来说并不总是显而易见的，这导致了对非泛型情况的正确解决方案的困惑，并且当它被丢弃时，对于 T 使用哪种类型的模糊性更是雪上加霜。.NET 5添加了一个非通用的 TaskCompletionSource ，这不仅消除了混淆，而且还有助于提高性能，因为它避免了需要为无用的 T 携带空间的任务。
    • Task.WhenAny(Task, Task) (dotnet/runtime#34288 and dotnet/runtime#37488). Previously, any number of tasks could be passed to Task.WhenAny via its overload that accepts a params Task[] tasks. However, in analyzing uses of this method, it was found that vast majority of call sites always passed two tasks. The new public overload optimizes for that case, and a neat thing about this overload is that just recompiling those call sites will cause the compiler to bind to the new faster overload instead of the old one, so no code changes are needed to benefit from the overload.
      Task.WhenAny(Task, Task) （dotnet/runtime#34288和dotnet/runtime#37488）。以前，任何数量的任务都可以通过接受 params Task[] tasks 的重载传递给 Task.WhenAny 。然而，在分析这种方法的用途时，发现绝大多数呼叫站点总是通过两个任务。新的公共重载针对这种情况进行了优化，而这个重载的一个巧妙之处在于，重新编译这些调用站点将导致编译器绑定到新的更快重载而不是旧的重载，因此不需要更改代码就能从重载中获益。
    private Task _incomplete = new TaskCompletionSource<bool>().Task;

[Benchmark]
public Task OneAlreadyCompleted() => Task.WhenAny(Task.CompletedTask, _incomplete);

    New Performance-focused Analyzers
    新型性能分析仪

    The C# “Roslyn” compiler has a very useful extension point called “analyzers”, or “Roslyn analyzers”. Analyzers plug into the compiler and are given full read access to all of the source the compiler is operating over as well as the compiler’s parsing and modeling of that code, which enables developers to plug in their own custom analyses to a compilation. On top of that, analyzers are not only runnable as part of builds but also in the IDE as the developer is writing their code, which enables analyzers to present suggestions, warnings, and errors on how the developer may improve their code. Analyzer developers can also author “fixers” that can be invoked in the IDE and automatically replace the flagged code with a “fixed” alternatives. And all of these components can be distributed via NuGet packages, making it easy for developers to consume arbitrary analyses written by others.
    C#“Roslyn”编译器有一个非常有用的扩展点，称为“analyzers”或“Roslyn analyzers”。分析器插入到编译器中，并且被赋予对编译器正在操作的所有源的完全读取访问权，以及编译器对该代码的解析和建模，这使得开发人员能够将他们自己的自定义分析插入到编译中。最重要的是，分析器不仅可以作为构建的一部分运行，而且可以在开发人员编写代码时在IDE中运行，这使分析器能够就开发人员如何改进其代码提出建议、警告和错误。Analyzer开发人员还可以编写可在IDE中调用的“修复程序”，并自动将标记的代码替换为“修复”替代品。所有这些组件都可以通过NuGet包分发，这样开发人员就可以轻松地使用其他人编写的任意分析。

    The Roslyn Analyzers repo contains a bunch of custom analyzers, including ports of the old FxCop rules. It also contains new analyzers, and for .NET 5, the .NET SDK will include a large number of these analyzers automatically, including brand new ones that have been written for this release. Multiple of these rules are either focused on or at least partially related to performance. Here are a few examples:
    Roslyn Analyzers仓库包含一堆自定义分析器，包括旧FxCop规则的端口。它还包含了新的分析器，对于.NET 5，.NET SDK将自动包含大量的这些分析器，包括为这个版本编写的全新分析器。这些规则中的多个要么集中在性能上，要么至少部分地与性能有关。以下是一些示例：

    • Detecting accidental allocations as part of range indexing. C# 8 introduced ranges, which make it easy to slice collections, e.g. someCollection[1..3]. Such an expression translates into either use of the collection’s indexer that takes a Range, e.g. public MyCollection this[Range r] { get; }, or if no such indexer is present, into use of a Slice(int start, int length). By convention and design guidelines, such indexers and slice methods should return the same type over which they’re defined, so for example slicing a T[] produces another T[], and slicing a Span<T> produces a Span<T>. This, however, can lead to unexpected allocations hiding because of implicit casts. For example, T[] can be implicitly cast to a Span<T>, but that also means that the result of slicing a T[] can be implicitly cast to a Span<T>, which means code like this Span<T> span = _array[1..3]; will compile and run fine, except that it will incur an array allocation for the array slice produced by the _array[1..3] range indexing. A more efficient way to write this would be Span<T> span = _array.AsSpan()[1..3]. This analyzer will detect several such cases and offer fixers to eliminate the allocation.  
    [Benchmark(Baseline = true)]
public ReadOnlySpan<char> Slice1()
{
    ReadOnlySpan<char> span = "hello world"[1..3];
    return span;
}

[Benchmark]
public ReadOnlySpan<char> Slice2()
{
    ReadOnlySpan<char> span = "hello world".AsSpan()[1..3];
    return span;
}

    • Prefer Memory overloads for Stream.Read/WriteAsync methods. .NET Core 2.1 added new overloads to Stream.ReadAsync and Stream.WriteAsync that operate on Memory<byte> and ReadOnlyMemory<byte>, respectively. This enables those methods to work with data from sources other than byte[], and also enables optimizations like being able to avoid pinning if the {ReadOnly}Memory<byte> was created in a manner that specified it represented already pinned or otherwise immovable data. However, the introduction of the new overloads also enabled a new opportunity to choose the return type for these methods, and we chose ValueTask<int> and ValueTask, respectively, rather than Task<int> and Task. The benefit of that is enabling more synchronously completing calls to be allocation-free, and even more asynchronously completing calls to be allocation-free (though with more effort on the part of the developer of the override). As a result, it’s frequently beneficial to prefer the newer overloads than the older ones, and this analyzer will detect use of the old and offer fixes to automatically switch to using the newer ones. dotnet/runtime#35941 has some examples of this fixing cases found in dotnet/runtime.
      对于 Stream.Read/WriteAsync 方法，首选 Memory 重载。.NET Core 2.1为 Stream.ReadAsync 和 Stream.WriteAsync 添加了新的重载，分别在 Memory<byte> 和 ReadOnlyMemory<byte> 上运行。这使得这些方法能够处理来自 byte[] 以外的源的数据，并且还实现了优化，例如如果 {ReadOnly}Memory<byte> 以指定其表示已经固定或以其他方式不可移动的数据的方式创建，则能够避免固定。然而，新重载的引入也为这些方法选择返回类型提供了新的机会，我们分别选择了 ValueTask<int> 和 ValueTask ，而不是 Task<int> 和 Task 。这样做的好处是使更多的同步完成的调用成为无分配的，甚至更多的异步完成的调用成为无分配的（尽管重写的开发人员需要付出更多的努力）。 因此，与旧的重载相比，更喜欢更新的重载通常是有益的，并且此分析器将检测旧重载的使用情况并提供修复以自动切换到使用新重载的重载。dotnet/runtime#35941有一些在dotnet/runtime中找到的修复案例的例子。
    private NetworkStream _client, _server;
private byte[] _buffer = new byte[10];

[GlobalSetup]
public void Setup()
{
    using Socket listener = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.Tcp);
    var client = new Socket(AddressFamily.InterNetwork, SocketType.Stream, ProtocolType.Tcp);
    listener.Bind(new IPEndPoint(IPAddress.Loopback, 0));
    listener.Listen();
    client.Connect(listener.LocalEndPoint);
    _client = new NetworkStream(client);
    _server = new NetworkStream(listener.Accept());
}

[Benchmark(Baseline = true)]
public async Task ReadWrite1()

    {

        await _server.ReadAsync(buffer, 0, buffer.Length); // may not read everything; just for demo purposes
    }
}

    • Prefer typed overloads on StringBuilder. StringBuilder.Append and StringBuilder.Insert have many overloads, for appending not just strings or objects but also various primitive types, like Int32.
